title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs one at a time, beating well. Combine salt and soda; add to oil mixture.
Stir in vanilla, apples, coconut and pecans.
Pour into tube pan sprayed with Pam and bake at 325° for 80 to 90 minutes.
Cool and serve.
Makes large cake and mellows with age.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish.

title: caramelitas
directions: Melt caramels and evaporated milk; mix with hands
all other ingredients except chips. Put half of mix in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chips on top, then pour caramels over chips.
Put rest of mix on top and bake until brown at 350°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add turnip, onions, ham knuckle, pepper and sugar.
Let cook until tender.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: In large bowl, add ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well. Gently shape into 1-inch balls.

title: very rocky road recipe(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart glass measure, cook sugar, 1 cup marshmallows, milk and margarine on High 1 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes until melted, stirring once during cooking.
Stir and cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla until smooth.
Fold nuts and remaining marshmallows.

title: maraschino cherry meringue topping
directions: Beat egg whites with vanilla and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar until stiff and glossy peaks form and all sugar is dissolved.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto banana or other flavored pudding.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Top each spoonful with 1/2 of a maraschino cherry.

title: potato-crust quiche
directions: Cook whole potatoes, covered, in boiling salted water for 20 to 25 minutes, or until tender.
Drain and peel.
Mash with a potato masher.
Measure 1 1/3 cups mashed potatoes.
Stir in butter or margarine.
Spoon into a greased 9-inch pie plate. Spread over bottom and up sides of pie plate, building up sides with a spoon to form a crust.
Arrange vegetables in bottom of potato crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: dilly beans
directions: Trim bean tips; pack lengthwise into 4 pint jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
To each pint, put 1/4 teaspoon pepper, 1 clove of garlic and 1 dill head.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to boiling.
Pour boiling hot over beans.
Adjust lids; process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Let stand for 2 weeks before tasting to allow the flavor to develop.

title: grilled chicken with mustard
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken. Place chicken in pan with mixture. Marinate 1 hour in refrigerator. Grill outdoors or broil for 10 to 15 minutes or until done in oven set at 350°. Baste often with marinade.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: I like to add chopped celery.

title: meat loaf with barbecue topping
directions: Mix the first four ingredients and take out 1/2 cup for the topping. Mix the rest of the barbecue sauce with the meat mixture.

title: luscious squares
directions: Spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: french green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans as directed on package.
Drain thoroughly and mix with soup.
Place in baking dish and top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
In 1 tablespoon bacon grease, cook onion until soft.
Add to pan the sugar, vinegar and water.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: texas style grits
directions: Cook grits according to box directions; add remaining ingredients and bake at 350°
for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: beat n' eat frosting
directions: Mix first four ingredients in small bowl.
Add boiling water. Beat to stiff peaks.
Spread over cake.
Makes 3 cups.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Peel and cut into sections zucchini.
Steam zucchini just long enough to soften.
Place zucchini in 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Top zucchini with Monterey Jack cheese.
Cover. Bake in 200° oven for approximately 5 minutes, just long enough to melt cheese.
Or, you may place in microwave for approximately 1 minute.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Boil potatoes.
Chill several hours.
Remove potato skins and grate coarsely.
Heat cream, salt, 1/3 stick margarine and cheese until cheese melts.
Mix with grated potatoes and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Top with sour cream and sprinkle with bacon bits.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.
Makes a good size casserole.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine 7-Up and ginger ale.
Add sherbet.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 7 x 11 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and salt with milk to make batter.
(If too stiff, add a little extra milk.)
Pour batter over butter.
Mix apple pie filling with raisins and smooth gently over batter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serve warm, topped with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: etouffee
directions: Melt margarine and saute onions.
Add flour (do not brown). Stir until smooth.
Add chicken broth, pepper and peeled shrimp. Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese soup
directions: Parboil potatoes, green pepper, broccoli and mushrooms just covered with water.
Cover with lid.
Drain water.
Add Velveeta and milk/water.
Cook until well blended.

title: cinnamon apricots in cream
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Halve and remove seeds from apricots. Place in a 1-quart casserole dish.
In small bowl, combine sugar, water and cinnamon.
Pour over fruit.
Bake 20 minutes or until apricots are tender.
Pour on cream and bake 5 minutes longer. Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all together and put in bake pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Let stand 1 hour. Drain all water off that you can.

title: rice medley
directions: Mix onions, celery and margarine together until tender. Combine with cooked rice, almonds, salt and thyme.
It is good served with turkey.

title: oreo freak out
directions: Place Oreos in bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan, then spread softened vanilla ice cream.
Then add layer of fudge sauce.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: pineapple upsidedown carrot cake
directions: 1. Drain pineapple (retain two slices pineapple & juice), melt 1/2 c. margarine in 10-inch ovenproof skillet; Blend in brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple and cherries over sugar mixture. 2. Beat remaining 1/4 c. margarine with granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg substitute, vanilla and carrots. 3. Chop remaining pineapple slices and add juice to make 1/3 c. and combine with dry ingredients. 4. Fold in raisins and walnuts.
Pour batter over pineapple.
Bake in oven for 350° for 40-45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before inverting on serving plate.

title: super broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble into small pieces.
Wash and cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
In a large bowl, combine broccoli, celery, onion, cauliflower and raisins; toss together.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour dressing over salad and mix.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: moist supper cake
directions: Pour hot Dr. Pepper over oatmeal and let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
With a mixer, cream shortening and gradually add in granulated sugar and 1 cup brown sugar.
Cream well; add eggs, beating until mixture is fluffy.

title: poor man's lobster 1
directions: Cover the fish with cold water and 2 tablespoons salt.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes, then drain.
Cover with cold water and 2 tablespoons vinegar.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain. Serve with melted butter.

title: fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly and bring to a boil.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Cool 5 minutes. Add vanilla and beat until creamy.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Cook chicken in water in skillet until tender.	Remove chicken from water.
Place chicken back in skillet.
Pour Open Pit barbecue sauce and 1/2 cup brown sugar over chicken.
Put into oven.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add beaten eggs, vanilla and applesauce.
Add spices and soda to sifted flour.
Add flour to other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: busy day soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and 1 medium onion.
Drain.
Put in crock-pot with other ingredients.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients. (For a softer, rounder cookie, add 1/2 cup flour.)

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add onions and bell pepper and saute; then add rice and salt.
Cook until tender.
Tomato sauce may be added.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Slice bananas in bottom of crust.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over bananas, evenly divided into 2 pies.
Spoon 1/2 can blueberry pie filling over top of each pie.
Keep refrigerated!

title: fluffy lemon pudding frosting
directions: Pour the milk into a large bowl. Add the pudding and pie filling.
Add the powdered sugar.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Stir in the Cool Whip.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Combine 4 ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla, salt and add nuts.
Pour on lightly buttered baking sheet; cool.
Separate into bite sized pieces.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 cups.

title: eggnog
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks.
Mix sugar and yolks.
Add liquor very, very slowly.
Whip egg whites and fold in.
Whip cream and fold in.

title: angel cookies
directions: Carefully melt almond bark. Pour over ingredients and mix until coated. Drop quickly by spoonful on wax paper.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine milk, sugar and salt.
Heat to scalding.
Dissolve yeast cake in warm water.
Beat egg.
Combine all ingredients and pour into flour.
Make into soft dough; let rise at room temperature until double in size.
Store in coldest part of refrigerator until ready to be used.
Shape into rolls and let rise at room temperature until double in size.
Bake in a hot 400° oven until done, about 12 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a Bundt pan.
Toss apples with 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Blend eggs, oil, vanilla, orange juice, 2 cups sugar, flour and salt. Add baking powder and baking soda.
Layer batter and apples alternately in pan, being careful not to touch apples to sides of pan.
The juice from the apples and cinnamon can be added in the layers.
Bake 1 hour.

title: holiday specials
directions: Cream the cream cheese and shortening.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Add egg and almond flavoring, beating until fluffy. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt and stir in.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: 1st Layer (Bottom):
1 pound cottage cheese and 8 ounces cream cheese (soft).

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Saute chicken in oil until done.
Don't overcook.
Place one layer of Doritos at bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place chicken on top of Doritos; pour mushroom soup over chicken; place one more layer of Doritos.
Next spread chilies, then grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or microwave until cheese melts and all is blended.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs and remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: stay-in-bed stew
directions: Bake 5 hours at 270° or 3 hours at 300°.
Great for crock-pot.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix the oil, margarine, eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Add the flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Make into balls and bake (if you want to, dust with granulated sugar).
Or you can roll out and cut out with cookie cutters, just add 1/2 cup more flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: curried chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put half and half and butter into 1-quart saucepan over moderate heat and bring to a boil.
In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch and sherry and slowly add to the saucepan, stirring vigorously to prevent lumping.
Add the curry powder, salt and cayenne pepper (if used) and cook until the sauce has boiled and thickened, about 3 minutes.
Add chicken; stir and remove from heat.
Cover the bottom of a buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish with rice; pour in chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Quick and easy.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Mix strawberries and sour cream; beat slowly until well mixed. Add vanilla and sugar while mixing until smooth consistency.
Add half and half last, mixing only until well blended.
Chill and serve.
Shake well before serving.
Serves 6.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix together and chill in refrigerator.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Pour 1 cup hot water over jello and stir until dissolved.
Mix the sugar with crushed pineapple and heat.
When cool, mix with jello.
Add cheese to jello when completely cold.
When set, add cream that has been whipped and stir.
Place in refrigerator until congealed.

title: molded salad
directions: Grease a large Bundt cake pan with Crisco (not oil).
Dissolve the strawberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and after cooling, place into the greased pan.
Allow to set before adding next layer of Jell-O.
Dissolve orange Jell-O in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1/4 cup juice from the fruit cocktail and allow to cool.
Add fruit from can and add to strawberry in mold after it has set.
Dissolve lime Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water and add to orange mixture after it has set.

title: basil salad dressing
directions: Combine dressing ingredients in a jar.
Shake to blend; chill. Serve over tossed salad.
Garnish salad with parsley.
Serves 20.

title: beans with spinach
directions: Soak beans in enough water to cover for 2
hours. Drain and cook in fresh unsalted water to cover until almost cooked.
Add the teaspoon of salt and cook until tender.
Drain.

title: pineapple spread
directions: Drain horseradish and combine with ingredients.
Pour over 8 ounces of cream cheese and serve as a spread with crackers.
Extra "spread" can be stored in jelly jars for 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water until dissolved. Add strawberries. Refrigerate until slightly jelled. Mix in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms, bell pepper and onion in butter.
Add ground beef and brown. Drain.
Mash tomatoes and add along with ketchup, tomato paste and Italian tomato sauce. Also add basil, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil then simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: frozen rainbow delight
directions: Whip the cream.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Combine crushed macaroons and nuts.
Fold into whipped cream.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with half of whipped cream mix.
Chill.
Layer sherbets and freeze after each layer.
Top with remaining whipped cream mixture.
Cover and freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Marinate 24 hours, turning twice.
Cook in moderate oven at 350° on cookie sheet 1/2 hour on each side until brown.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Pat chicken
breasts
dry and dredge in flour, seasoned with salt
and pepper.
Sprinkle oregano over chicken breasts. Heat oil and
butter in heavy skillet and brown chicken.
When brown on both
sides add wine and cover.
Simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle
Parmesan over chicken before serving. Serves 4.

title: gravlaks
directions: Rub fish with oil.
Mix sugar, salt and pepper.
Lightly rub on fish.
Lay fish, skin down, in glass baking dish.
Pat rest of mixture on top of fish; spoon cognac over it.
Place onion and 2 cups dill on top of fish.
Cover dish with plastic wrap.
Chill 12 hours, basting fish with accumulating juices 3 to 4 times.
Turn fish over with onion and dill under it.
Cover and chill 12 more hours, basting with juices 3 to 4 times.
After 24 hours fish is ready to serve.
Slice paper thin or remove from brine and keep in refrigerator.

title: simple thick white sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth. Gradually stir in milk.
Stir constantly until thick.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Trim chops and brown in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Arrange potatoes and carrots around chops.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops and vegetables.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: harvard beets
directions: Heat beets with liquid.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar. Stir into beets. Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth, clear and thickened.

title: long lasting slaw
directions: Bring bell pepper, onion, sugar, vinegar, Crisco and salt to a boil.
Then pour over the grated cabbage.
If you like, you can grate 2 large carrots with cabbage.
This gives color and adds taste. This will keep in the refrigerator for two weeks.

title: "lyn's" wonderful chicken
directions: Mix together the chicken and cream cheese.
Mix together the broth and soup.
Unroll the rolls and spoon chicken mixture onto wide end of roll.
Continue until all chicken is used.
Place rolls in Pam coated pan.
Pour soup on top of rolls and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover to brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with 1 stick of margarine.
Press into 9 x 13- x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs, powdered sugar and 2 sticks of margarine together for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Dice 4 bananas over, then spread pineapple over bananas.
Spread topping over pineapple.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries. Refrigerate overnight.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
In blender, add stems and remaining ingredients.
Stuff mushroom caps.
Place on a baking sheet.
Sprinkle oil lightly over mushrooms.
Bake 350° about 45 mins.
Top each with mozzarella and bake additional 10-15 mins.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs and mix until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar into second bowl.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture until well mixed.
Refrigerate dough for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in order given.
Drop by large tablespoonfuls or by ice cream scoop and flatten. Bake for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: lazy day bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight. Drain. Add 2 qts. water, onion, and meat. Simmer 3 hrs. In other pan simmer tomatoes, chili pow- der lemon juice, salt, pepper, liquid smoke 30 min. Add to beans and simmer together 40 more min.

title: peaches 'n cream pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Press down and up sides of plate (to make crust). Drain peaches (reserve 3 tablespoons).
Combine remaining ingredients (cream cheese and sugar).
Mix 2 minutes. Pour on top of "crust."
Place peaches on top (decoratively). Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Do not brown.

title: caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Set aside popped corn and peanuts in large brown bag. Mix sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart glass bowl. Cook in microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes. Stir each minute until boils. Cook 2 minutes more. Take out; stir in baking soda. Pour in sack over popcorn and peanuts. Shake sack. Put sack in microwave. Cook on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes. Take out and shake bag. Put sack back in microwave. Cook 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Spread and separate caramel corn on sheet of aluminum foil. Let cool. Place in airtight container for storing.

title: microwave coconut cream pie
directions: Pour evaporated milk into 4 cup measure.
Add milk, pudding mix and 1/2 cup of the coconut.
Stir briskly.
Cook on High, 6 to 7 minutes, stirring once.
Pour into crumb crust.
Set aside. Place remaining coconut in1
cup glass measure.
Add butter.
Cook on High thoroughly.
Coconut should be lightly browned.
Sprinkle coconut over pie filling.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 6 servings.
Cooking Time:
8 to 9 minutes.

title: mandarin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: party pink champagne
directions: Pour all ingredients over ice in punch bowl.
Serve at once.

title: tamale pie(serves 8+)
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Grate cheese.
Chop onions.
Chop tamales in small pieces.
Layer tamales, corn, beef, tomatoes, olives and onions.
Make approximately 3 layers, ending with tamales.
Put grated cheese on top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon spiced banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with nonstick spray and set aside.

title: nana bette's carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Add the next 4 ingredients and beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in next 4 ingredients until blended.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Press lightly in center for doneness.
Cool completely.

title: seafood supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: vermont spring chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered 50 to 60 minutes at 400°.
Baste.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot. Simmer 2 hours. Refrigerate at least 24 hours before reheating to serve.

title: stuffed salisbury steak
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and saute celery and onion until tender.
Add water and bring to a boil; add stuffing mix.
Remove from heat and stir until blended.
Combine evaporated milk and meat.
Divide into 6 portions on waxed paper.
Pat into a 5-inch circle.
Put 1/6 of stuffing mix in center of each patty.
Draw edges of meat over mix and seal.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: brownies
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder, cocoa and sugar.
Add eggs, butter and vanilla.
Grease pan with butter and pour in mixture. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: three layer dessert
directions: Mix margarine and flour like pie dough.
Press into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Press chopped nuts into dough.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: roasted eggplant and tomato soup
directions: Drain tomatoes and reserve juice.
Cut eggplant lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Lay slices on paper towels or in a colander and sprinkle with salt.
Set aside for 1 hour.
Preheat broiler or grill.
Wipe excess liquid off eggplant slices.
Brush both sides with olive oil.
Place slices on a broiler rack or cookie sheet and broil eggplant as close to heat as possible until golden brown on both sides, or grill over medium hot coals until brown.
Place tomatoes in blender or food processor.
Add a few eggplant slices, puree, adding eggplant slices and reserved tomato juice, until soup is of desired consistency and taste.
Heat before serving.
Serve garnished with grated Parmesan cheese. Serves 6 to 8.
Before broiling, eggplant may be sprinkled with any of the following:
dried basil, pepper, coriander, crushed garlic, parsley, oregano or thyme.

title: raspberry sorbet
directions: Puree
raspberries in a food processor.
Strain through a fine
sieve
into a mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir
until
sugar	dissolves.
Freeze in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pat into greased pizza pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: best baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients. Put in large casserole or 2 medium. Cover and bake in slow oven at 325° for 3 hours, stirring occasionally. Uncover the last 30 minutes of cooking. Serves 20. Can make 1/2 recipe if want smaller amount.

title: honey bunn cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; pour 1/2 of the mixture in 9 x 13 pan. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle sugar mixture on cake batter and pour remaining cake batter on top of sugar. Swirl through cake with a knife. Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pear preserves cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush bottom and sides of crust evenly with egg yolk.
Bake on baking sheet until light brown, about 5 minutes.

title: no cook divinity
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine frosting mix (dry), corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water.
Beat on highest speed until stiff peaks form; about 5 minutes.
Transfer to large mixing bowl; on low speed, gradually blend in sugar; stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
When outside of candy feels firm, turn over.
Dry at least 12 hours.
Store candy in airtight container.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In a skillet, over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry half of the chicken until browned.
Remove.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Over medium heat, in remaining 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry vegetables with ginger and garlic powder until tender-crisp.
Add soup, soy sauce and vinegar.
Heat to boiling. Return chicken to skillet.
Heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pineapple and pistachio pudding into a bowl and mix well.
Fold in whipped topping and stir in marshmallows and nuts. Chill 1 hour.

title: delicious and easy potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, mix hash browns, soup, melted butter, sour cream, cheese, garlic powder, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and put in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: baked yellow squash
directions: Pour melted butter into a 9-inch pan or baking dish.
Add lemon juice, thyme, salt and pepper to the butter.
Stir with fork until mixed.
Place squash in pan, cut side down.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until squash is tender or microwave in a Pyrex dish for about 8 minutes.
Turn once.

title: spinach-tomato casserole
directions: Thaw spinach in microwave and squeeze out all water.
Beat eggs with milk, Ricotta cheese and bread crumbs.
Add spinach and mix well.
Use 13 x 9-inch casserole dish; spray with Pam and cover bottom of dish with tomatoes.
Spread spinach mixture over tomatoes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake a 375° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, nectar, oil and sugar well.
Bake at 350° for one hour or less.

title: layered salad
directions: Cook peas until tender.
Fry bacon until crisp.
(May substitute bacon bits in jar for bacon.)
Drain peas.

title: mom's summer cucumbers
directions: Mix together and keep refrigerated.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cream margarine, egg and sweetener.
Add baking powder, spices, flour and (I like pineapple the best) applesauce or pineapple.
Mix well.
Fold in dates and nuts.
(I leave nuts out to save on calories.)
Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Spray pan well before pouring batter in pan.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
This cake must be kept refrigerated.

title: blueberry oat muffins
directions: Combine oats and milk; let stand a few minutes.
In another bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in egg, butter and oat mixture.
When mixed, gently fold in the blueberries.
Fill well-greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with whole graham crackers.
Combine sugar, butter and pecans in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Take out of oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let cool about 30 minutes.
Cut and transfer to wax paper for chocolate chips to cool completely before stacking.
Refrigerate.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and slice lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices. Salt slices, place in colander and allow to stand for 30 minutes. Wash off salt and dry slices.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Fill crust.
Freeze in freezer. Thaw 1/2 hour before serving.

title: cream pie with meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar together in medium saucepan.
Add milk to cornstarch and sugar mixture; then add beaten egg yolks and mix together.
Place on stove over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Mixture will thicken.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and stir to combine.
Pour into baked 8-inch pie shell.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine strawberry gelatin, cornstarch and sugar in saucepan; add water.
Cook, while stirring, over medium heat until clear and thick.
Cool.

title: cheese puffs with sausage
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Makes approximately 70 balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve with mustard.
These freeze well.

title: hearty tuna casserole
directions: Drain tuna and flake.
Cook noodles; drain and rinse.
Combine noodles, tuna, celery and onion.
Blend sour cream, mustard, mayo, salt and thyme.
Spoon 1/2 mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 the zucchini.
Repeat layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped tomato.

title: chicken gourmet
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half.
Melt margarine in heavy frying pan.
Blend in garlic, salt, chili powder, pepper and dry mustard.
Brown chicken breasts on both sides.
Cover pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes until tender.
Place on heated platter.
Add flour to pan juices and stir until thick. Slowly pour in cream and milk and stir until it thickens.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon over chicken breasts.

title: ham with apple-kraut
directions: You may use smoked pork chops in place of ham.

title: apple-oatmeal pan cookies(35 squares)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips, oats, apples and cinnamon.
Spread in ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain well.
Put in a large crock-pot along with the other ingredients and cook until cheese has melted. Serve with nacho chips or Doritos or over hot dogs.

title: basic white sauce
directions: In 1-quart pot, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper, making a smooth paste.
Slowly add milk; blend well.
Cook until sauce is thickened and bubbly, stirring often.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour which has been sifted with baking powder.
Add milk.
Add flavoring; beat well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Fill paper cupcakes 2/3 full.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, salt and eggs.
Stir in chocolate pieces.

title: pork lo mein
directions: Preheat wok and add oil.
Cook noodles until tender and set aside.
Stir-fry garlic and onions for 1 minute, then remove.
Add more oil if necessary.
Add 1/2 the pork for 2 to 3 minutes, remove from pan then do rest of pork.
Then add all the ingredients together, then add noodles!!!!
Sit and enjoy!!!!!

title: easy lemon dessert
directions: Blend into a dough and pat on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts; cool and cut into pieces.
Saute carrots and celery in 1 stick oleo.
Mix chicken base with 1 to 1 1/2 gallons water; add carrots, celery and chicken pieces.
Boil until vegetables are done; add noodles and cook until noodles are done. Make thickening by melting 2 sticks of oleo and adding flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add this to soup, making sure all lumps are dissolved.
Remove from heat and let stand about 1/2 hour.
Add whipping cream and stir until it is all mixed in.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup, onion, pimento, celery, almonds, water chestnuts and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: one-eyed pirates
directions: Take a glass and cut a hole around glass on bread.
The bread should now have a hole in the middle.
Melt margarine in a large skillet on medium heat and add the bread slices.
Brown the bread for 2 to 3 minutes.
Crack the eggs and drop into the holes of the bread.
Cook for 1 minute, then flip the bread and egg to brown other side.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning together and pour into pie plate.
Top with remaining ingredients. Refrigerate and serve with nacho chips.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together in order. Bake in preheated oven until golden brown.
Makes 10 servings.

title: peanut butter candy(hardtack)
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and water to boil (300°).
Put peanut butter in round iron skillet (butter pan).
Pour syrup over peanut buter. Cut in squares.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and pour into an 8-inch Pyrex. Combine all remaining ingredients except butter.
Sprinkle dry mixture over apple mixture.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel large potatoes and slice.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice onions into rings and mix with potatoes.
Pour milk over potatoes until covered.
Grate Longhorn Colby cheese or cheese of your choice.
Layer top of dish with cheese.
Add salt and pepper to top.
Bake in 375° oven until potatoes stick tender with fork, approximately 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew or bake the chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from the bone into small pieces.
Using a medium to large baking dish or pan, put one layer of chicken in the bottom.
Pour over it 1/2 can of the soup.
Add 1 layer of dressing.
Then add another layer of chicken, balance of soup and a layer of dressing.
Pour chicken broth over it.
Do not cover.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 40 to 45 minutes or until well browned.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables, tossing lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.

title: quick and easy cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add margarine and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, eggs, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured 8-inch layer pans or one 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers, 40 to 45 minutes for square cake.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Wash, clean and cut up tomatoes.
Chop onions, celery, parsley and bay leaves.
Add to tomatoes.
Cook until celery is tender. Put through sieve.
Make a thin paste of the flour and butter, using a little of the tomato juice.
Add to boiling soup.
Keep stirring to prevent scorching.
Add salt, sugar and pepper.
If it is lumpy, put through sieve again.
Fill pint jars.
Put on lids tightly.
Hot water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes 10 pints.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Line 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan wells with paper baking cups. Mix together the sour cream, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Blend in walnuts and the well-drained pineapple and cherries.
Peel and dice the banana and quickly mix into fruit mixture.
Spoon into baking cups; place
in freezer or freezing compartment of refrigerator until firm.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add onions and cook over medium heat until tender, but not brown (about 10 minutes).
Add salt, broth and water.
Stir well.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sugar cookie recipe
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter. Add sugar slowly and cream until fluffy.
Stir in well beaten egg yolks and vanilla extract.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with cream.
Chill for one hour.
Roll and cut in any desired shape.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stir-fried crickets
directions: Note:
A good source of crickets is a pet shop.
Larger quantities are less per dozen, so you may want to stock up!
It is not recommended to catch your own, they may be contaminated by pesticides.
Pet shop crickets are usually raised by breeders. (Ask to be sure.)

title: quick fudge frosting
directions: Pour dry ingredients; mix together and add 6 tablespoons boiling water, vanilla and butter.
Blend, then beat with mixer or spoon until smooth and thickened.
If frosting stiffens too quickly while spreading, just stir in a few drops of hot water.

title: "nine's" chocolate pudding
directions: In the top of a double boiler, put sugar, salt and flour. Stir in 1/3 cup milk (remainder to be used later) and beaten egg yolks.
Mix until well blended.
Add remaining milk and cocoa. Cook, until thick, stirring constantly.

title: apricot cheese delight
directions: Drain fruit.
Keep apricot and pineapple juice separate. Chill fruit.
Dissolve jello in hot water and add apricot juice. Fold in apricots, pineapple and mini marshmallows.
Chill until firm, then add topping.

title: ginger chicken hips marina
directions: Mix together vermouth, soy sauce, sugar and flavor enhancer. Heat corn oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken, skin side down, and ginger; brown chicken on all sides. Remove oil from skillet, except for 2 tablespoons. Pour seasoning mixture over chicken. Cover and cook about 7 minutes. Remove ginger. Sprinkle scallion over chicken and serve. Serves 6.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine, and cream cheese with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flavorings and then add cake flour.
Mix well.
Bake at 250 degrees for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: newspaper papier-mache
directions: In a bucket or bowl, mix water and flour to form a sticky, gooey paste.
Tear newspaper into strips about 1 or 2 inches wide - ragged edges stick together better.
Add strips to paste, a handful at a time.
Squeeze the paste and paper together till the mixture is mushy.
When the mass is slippery and sticks together well, you've got papier-mache.
If it's not slippery, add more paste.

title: cinnamon biskins
directions: Mix.
Roll out like biscuits.
Place on cookie sheet about 2 inches part.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: no cook candy
directions: Blend milk and vanilla. Slowly add sugar and stir.
Roll into small balls. Then roll in crushed nuts and coconut.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients; crumble and press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Blend next 3 ingredients together and pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: gingered chicken with vegetables
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in large skillet over medium-high heat. Stir-fry chicken until no longer pink. Remove chicken from skillet. Heat remaining 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in skillet. Add red pepper, mushrooms, pea pods, water chestnuts, green onion, ginger and garlic. Stir-fry mixture 3 to 4 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender. Meanwhile, combine chicken broth, Equal, soy sauce, cornstarch and sesame oil until smooth. Cook over medium heat until thick and clear. Stir in chicken; heat thoroughly. Season with salt and pepper, if desired. Serves

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add other ingredients, beating well.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: geecheed cabbage with tomatoes
directions: In a
big
heavy pot fry bacon, green peppers and onion until crisp.
Add
everything
else and stir well. Cook until heated through.
Serve
over rice for the best and only way to get Geechee flavor.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cruellers
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix all dry ingredients and sift.
Add to first mixture.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut in triangle.
Slit in middle.
Pull dough through slit and shape.
Fry in hot oil or shortening until brown on both sides. Drain on paper.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool, then serve.

title: spiced sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in nonstick casserole. Combine sugar substitute, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Exchanges:
1 bread, 1/2 fat.
Serving:
1/3 cup.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water according to package directions. Drain.
In a skillet, saute chuck, green pepper and onion until slightly browned. Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Stir cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream into noodles.
In a 3-quart casserole, spread half of the noodles and top with half the meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake at
375° until bubbly.

title: bara brith - fruit cake
directions: Place fruit and nuts in a large bowl.
Pour tea over fruit. Add brown sugar and mix well.
Cover fruit mixture and let stand over-night at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare a 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan with cooking spray or grease.
Add remaining ingredients (flour through cinnamon) to soaked fruit. Stir until combined.

title: no bake while you sleep cookies
directions: Beat egg whites slightly.
Add sugar and beat into stiff peaks. Fold in remaining ingredients.
Place aluminum foil on 2 cookie sheets and drop cookies by teaspoons on foil.
Preheat oven to 350°.
When cookies are placed in oven, turn oven off.
Leave overnight or at least 6 hours.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and blend until light and fluffy. Add flour, salt, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well.
Chill dough.
To shape cookies, take a teaspoon of dough and roll to finger shape. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 325° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll in confectioners sugar before cooling.
Roll again when cooled.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: mushroom appetizer
directions: Saute cleaned mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes. Sprinkle in the dressing mix. Add lemon. Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours. Serve hot with toothpicks.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla. Whip whipping cream until peaks form. Fold into cream cheese mixture and pour into pie crust. Cool for 24 hours. Top with fruit and serve. May be frozen for later use.

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend together and roll in chopped pecans.
This is great with crackers.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef. Add all ingredients in large saucepan and cook slow. Serve with chips, cheese and sour cream.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and salt.
Sift flour and soda; beat into creamed mixture.
Add pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan well.
Pour in the batter.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° until cake is done, about 30 minutes.

title: dave's chocolate fudge
directions: Blend ingredients together and boil to soft ball stage.
Cool and add vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: mrs. trant's squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain and mash.
Layer squash and onion.
Mix eggs and butter.
Pour over squash.
Top with cream of mushroom soup.
Sprinkle cheese over soup.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Set aside and let soften.
Leave sausage at room temperature until soft.
Put all 3 ingredients in large bowl. Squeeze with hands until mixed.
Put in fridge until it gets firm.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix rhubarb, 1/4 cup flour, water, sugar and cinnamon together and put in 9 inch pan. Mix
1 cup flour, brown sugar, rolled oats and melted butter and pour over rhubarb mixture. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: old fashion cream cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions and drain.
Add corn, cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese before baking, if desired.

title: hot dried beef dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: best gravy in town
directions: Mix soups together with 1/2 can milk.
Add chopped eggs and butter; mix well.
Heat on low.
Giblets may be added to gravy.

title: sweet cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add one egg at a time.
Add flour and baking powder.
Finally, add flavoring, cream and whiskey gradually and mix well.

title: creme de menthe bars
directions: Mix together and spread in jelly roll pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gourmet grahams
directions: Melt butter and margarine.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add chopped nuts.
Pour over graham crackers that have been broken into 4 pieces from each whole cracker and placed
in an 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan.
Carefully remove each cracker with a spatula.
Yield: 48.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breast
well done, let cool and dice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Combine celery, onion, green pepper and relish.
Mix well.	Blend well with mayonnaise.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour and Crisco.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to flour and Crisco; add buttermilk and enough cold water to make a dough.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream cheese and powdered sugar; add peanut butter and beat until fluffy.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie crust and refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring juice and enough water to a boil to make 1 3/4 cups hot liquid.
Mix in jello until it dissolves.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and chill until set.
Great served with ham, chicken or turkey.

title: chocolate peanut bonbons
directions: Roll into balls.
For coating, melt 6 ounces chocolate chips and 1/3 bar of paraffin.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and lay out on wax paper to harden.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes, white sugar, beaten eggs, vanilla and melted butter.
Put in baking dish.

title: crock chili
directions: In a large saucepan, brown meat and drain on paper towels. Put all ingredients in 4-quart crock-pot and stir well.
Cover and cook on low heat 10 to 12 hours. Yields 12 cups.
Serve with your favorite toppings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Place meat, chopped eggs, celery, salt and mayonnaise in a cold bowl.
Mix well with a fork.
Serve on crisp lettuce, garnished with several stuffed olives.

title: christmas vegetable salad
directions: Steam broccoli in saucepan for 2 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Rinse immediately in ice water.
Combine with cauliflower, red pepper and onion in bowl with airtight lid.
Add salad dressing and pepper; mix well.
Chill, covered, for 24 hours or longer, stirring occasionally.
Yields 8 servings.

title: creamy chicken vegetable chowder
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, combine milk, chicken broth, cream of potato soup and cream of chicken soup; blend well.
Add remaining chowder ingredients, except cheese; mix well.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese; stir until melted.

title: pie crust
directions: Put lard in medium bowl.
Add water and milk.
Break up lard with 4 prong fork.
Tilt bowl and beat with fork in quick cross-the-bowl strokes until mixture is smooth like whipped cream and holds soft peaks.
Sift flour and salt on top of mixture with vigorous, round the bowl strokes, stirring quickly, forming dough that clings together and cleans bowl.
Pick up dough and work it into a smooth round ball.
Divide in half.
Roll out on floured board.
Lift and sprinkle flour under it if it tends to stick. Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness.
Do not grease pie pan, but dust flour over it lightly.
Trim excess dough from outside edges with a knife.
Prick holes around sides and in center with fork.
Bake until light brown.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Add sharp Velveeta and white American cheese to taste.
Put into greased casserole; cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are brown.

title: shrimp-crab casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add thyme, curry powder, Worcestershire, Heinz 57 and 1/2 cup dressing.
Add enough mayonnaise to hold mixture together.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Top with remaining Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Dot with butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 large servings.

title: apple-pecan crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased casserole and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix other ingredients until crumbly and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: hummus
directions: Blend in the blender, pushing down with a spatula.
Turn into a bowl.
Pour a thick layer of olive oil over the top, 1/4 inch deep, then a layer of lemon juice.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Serve with pita bread as a dip or drop into falafels inside the pita bread with chopped tomatoes and alfalfa sprouts.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Bake fish 15 minutes at 350°.
In shallow dish, mix crumbs, paprika, Parmesan cheese and pepper or chili powder.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise and green onion.
Brush both sides of fillets (after drying with paper towels) with mayonnaise.
Coat with crumbs.
Arrange in single layer in baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: hobo bread
directions: Soak raisins and baking soda in water overnight.
Add brown and granulated sugars, oil, flour and salt.
Bake in 3 greased 1-pound cans for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sage balls
directions: Grate the cheese.
Mix all ingredients together and roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and brown in a 350° oven.

title: 14 day pickles in 5 minutes
directions: Drain pickles and cut into chunks.
Combine sugar, vinegar and pickling spices in a small saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pack pickles in jar and add sugar mixture. Cover, cool and refrigerate.
Makes 1 quart.

title: mama's cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal mix and baking soda.
Mix in egg, oil and buttermilk.
Bake in a greased preheated iron skillet at 450° until golden brown.

title: ratatouille
directions: In 4 or 5-quart Dutch oven or large pot, heat oil until hot. Add onions, garlic, eggplant and peppers and cook over medium heat, stirring often until onions are crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in zucchini, tomatoes, parsley and basil.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium, cover and cook 15 minutes. Remove cover and stir in seasoned salt and pepper.
Continue cooking, uncovered, 10 minutes longer.
Stir in tomato paste. Serve as is or over hot cooked rice.
Top each serving with a sprinkling of shredded cheese.

title: waldorf salad mckay
directions: Mix apples, pineapple, raisins and walnuts together in a bowl. Stir honey into yogurt and add cinnamon to one's taste.

title: heavenly angel biscuits
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in the 1/2 cup warm water.
Combine oil, milk, sugar and yeast-water.
Add to dry flour mixture and mix well until all flour is moistened.
When ready to use, roll out on floured surface to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness and cut.
Place on greased cookie sheet or shallow pan. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown...Heavenly!! Refrigerate leftover dough in a covered bowl.
Keeps about a week.
(Can have hot biscuits everyday!!)

title: bow wow dog biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into a ball.
Wrap in plastic paper and refrigerate overnight.

title: rigatoni with tomato vodka lemon sauce
directions: Cook the 2 pound rigatoni.
While the rigatoni is cooking, prepare the tomato, vodka and lemon sauce by following these directions.
In a large skillet, heat the olive oil; add butter. When the bubbles have disappeared, add Prosciutto, sliced thinly and torn into 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Allow to cook for a minute or so.
Now it's time to add the tomatoes which have been seeded and sliced into 1/8-inch pieces along with very thin lemon slices (half the size of the tomatoes slices, also seeded).
Saute for a couple of minutes before adding the finely chopped garlic.
Pour in the vodka; simmer for a couple of more minutes until the tomatoes and lemon wilt.
At this point, add the marinara sauce and stir the contents together.
Next add the heavy cream and stir until the sauce is heated throughout.
Adjust salt and pepper to taste.
Drain the rigatoni and mix with the sauce in a large bowl.

title: spiced pumpkin bread
directions: Beat butter at medium speed of mixer.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add molasses, orange juice and pumpkin.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture; mix until blended.
Stir in vanilla, raisins and nuts.

title: hotel juana's roasted monkfish with thyme flowers, spinach and red(ingredients for 4 persons)
directions: Remove the filets from the monkfish and brush with olive oil and fresh thyme flowers.
Peel the 3 half pepper and cut in large julienne.
Cook in boiling salted water; refresh in ice water and drain.
Reheat just before serving in a saucepan with olive oil. Make the red pepper coulis.
Season the monkfish filets with salt and pepper.
In a Teflon frying pan, add olive oil, 2 cloves garlic and lightly brown the filets, finishing the cooking in the oven. When done, set aside covered with aluminum foil.

title: diane's cheeseburger loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients, except cheese.
Line loaf pan with foil.
Evenly spread 1/2 of the cheese in bottom of pan.
Cover with 1/2 the meat mixture.
Repeat with remaining cheese and meat mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together baking powder, flour, sugar and salt. Add egg, milk and corn; mix. Drop in oil at 365°. Turn once. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Takes only 3 to 4 minutes to cook.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries.
Mix with sugar; set overnight.
Drain off any juice.
Mix marshmallows, Cool Whip and nuts with chopped cranberries.
Chill and serve.

title: curry chicken
directions: Cut chicken into medium pieces.
Squeeze a half lemon or lime on chicken; mix together and set aside.
In Dutch oven or large pot, put oil and garlic (cut fine).
Let garlic brown; cut onion and add to garlic.
Fry for 1 minute.
Rinse chicken twice and add it to the onion and garlic; stir.
Add curry powder, water, coconut milk, pepper, potatoes and salt to taste.
Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
When potatoes are cooked, it's finished.
Serve on rice.

title: baked lamb chops
directions: Melt butter in a heavy skillet; brown lamb chops. Place chops in a baking dish; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour 1/2 cup water into the skillet and stir to loosen browned bits. Add remaining ingredients to skillet then pour over the lamb chops. Cover and bake at 350 for 1 hour. Serves 3.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Beat eggs, milk and salt until fluffy.
Add ingredients remaining; mix well.
Pour into lightly baked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lazy womans stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown meat, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix in rice.
Put half of cabbage in bottom of 9 x 13 baking pan.
Spread with meat filling.
Cover with rest of cabbage.
Mix water and tomato soup. Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon wheels
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or knives until mixture is like coarse cornmeal.
Add milk and mix together with rubber spatula until dough holds together and forms a ball.
Place dough on lightly floured board and knead 10 to 12 times.

title: wassail
directions: Combine and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add red coloring if desired.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks under refrigeration.

title: zucchini "apple" pie
directions: Use large (tender) zucchini.
Peel and cut in quarters lengthwise.
Remove seeds and slice crosswise.
These will resemble apple slices.
Cook until just tender-crisp.
Drain. Toss with dash of salt and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Have mixed in a bowl the sugar, cinnamon, cream of tartar, dash of nutmeg and flour. Add zucchini.
Place in 9-inch rich crust.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until fluffy.
Store in refrigerator. Serves 8 to 12.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Sear chops on both sides until brown in skillet with no grease. When chops
are
brown on both sides, turn, add sliced ingredients.
Add tomato juice.
A little more salt and pepper may be needed.
Turn
heat
and simmer on low.
Cook, covered, for about 1 hour.
Then serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil noodles and drain.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Heat in oven until cheese melts. Serve.

title: morrett glop
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add tomato soup, green beans and corn.
Simmer 30 minutes covered.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add melted margarine and other ingredients. Cook at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: mother's pie crust
directions: Combine water and oil; allow to come to a boil.
Remove from heat; add flour.
Mix well and pat into pie pan.
Bake before adding pie mixture.

title: jalapeno appetizer
directions: Pam a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish and line the bottom with drained, sliced jalapeno hot peppers.
Grate Cheddar cheese and put on top of the peppers.
Beat eggs and pour over top of cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut in 1-inch squares.

title: lemon bread with glaze
directions: Blend butter and 1 cup of the sugar; beat in eggs one at a time. Add almond ext. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with the milk. Blend lightly, fold in peel and nuts. Bake in a glass loaf pan at 325 for about 70 minutes.

title: meatball dinner
directions: Soften bread in milk.
Add egg.
Mix rest.
Make 18 balls. Roll in flour.
Brown in hot shortening; drain.
Add tomato juice, water, carrots, celery, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice, potatoes or noodles. Serves 6.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a large 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sugar, milk and flour together and pour over margarine.
Pour the hot fruit over batter and bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: minestrone
directions: Brown potato, onion and carrot in hot oil until lightly golden.
Add and mix tomatoes, broth, sauce and macaroni; bring to a boil, breaking up tomatoes while stirring.
Reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese before serving, if desired.
6 servings.

title: saucy chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients together except chicken to make a sauce.
Put chicken in a heavy saucepan, cover with sauce and simmer for 40 minutes over medium heat.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in 2 graham cracker crusts. Chill good before serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat eggs and add to flour mixture.
Add melted butter, buttermilk, salt and vanilla to mixture and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until pie is firm and brown on top, about 30 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook and stir onion and bacon in 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender and bacon is crisp.
Add enough water to clam liquid to measure 1 cup.
Stir clams, liquid, potatoes, salt and pepper into onion mixture.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in milk and heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: dorothy's fruit cobbler
directions: Pour fruit into baking pan, Mix flour, sugar, milk and butter together and pour over fruit.
Bake in 400 degree oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add tomato sauce, catsup, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and oregano; cook 20 minutes. Split rolls.
Spread with garlic spread on both sides.
Add meat, then cheese.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350` for 15 minutes.

title: banana trifle
directions: Place vanilla wafers (except 1/2 cup finely crushed) in 9 x 13-inch dish, then set aside.
Combine pudding and milk; beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Add sour cream and half of the Cool Whip; mix well. Place half pudding over wafers and smooth around.
Slice bananas over pudding, then cover with remaining pudding; smooth, then cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Smooth, then sprinkle finely crushed vanilla wafers over top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pasta salad
directions: Put olive oil in a dish.
Add pasta and seasonings.
Cook in microwave for 5 minutes.
Add Wish-Bone dressing and sugar. Serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Combine first four ingredients and boil for 2 to 3 minutes. Add butter and vanilla.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown sausage; pour off some grease.
Add onion, pepper and celery.
Stir in soup and rice.
Add 4 1/2 cups boiling water. Cook slowly until rice is tender (45 minutes).
Add water if needed.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, cornstarch and
sugar
in
top
of double boiler.
Add milk, water
and
slightly beaten egg yolks, stirring well.
Cook in double boiler over medium heat until thick. Add vanilla and butter.
Pour
into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff;
add 4 tablespoons sugar.
Spread over pie.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Dip from teaspoon into hot fat and fry until brown on both sides.

title: blueberry oatmeal muffins(a family favorite adapted from the three rivers cookbook)
directions: Mix oats and milk together and leave for 30 minutes at room temperature.
Add the brown sugar, oil and egg to oat/milk mixture and stir well.
Gently fold in the flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Then add blueberries.
Spoon into 12 muffin tins with papers and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned date nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a large spoon to cream sugar and butter by hand.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add dates and nuts.
Coat nuts and dates well with dough.
Using a teaspoon, drop dough onto an ungreased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour over browned pieces of chicken in saucepan.
Simmer 1 hour.
Also great for leftover fried chicken.

title: sugar-free punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water and pineapple juice. Chill. Combine in punch bowl with the diet Sprite. Makes about 1 gallon.

title: chicken spoon bread
directions: Measure corn meal; set aside.
Heat milk, butter, onions and seasoning in a large saucepan until butter melts.
Gradually stir in corn meal.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils.
Cook for one minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool. Stir in chicken pieces, then egg yolks; mix thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into corn meal mixture. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Top with chicken gravy, if desired.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together and set aside.
Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add sugar and blend well. Add salad oil; gradually stir in flour. Add milk, poppy seed filling and nuts. Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: squash fritters
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender. Drain all water; get as much water out as possible. Add 1 egg, salt and pepper to taste. Add flour slowly until mixture is the consistency of hush puppies. Spoon into hot grease and fry until golden brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, onions and peppers.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 1 hour; drain off liquid.
Mix in saucepan the remaining ingredients; bring to a hard boil.
Add squash, onions and peppers. Bring to another boil.
Fill jars and seal.
Makes four pints.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix all together. Refrigerate overnight.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Place first three ingredients in a bowl.
Sprinkle jello over top.
Stir until jello color is evenly distributed.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate jumbles
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add molasses, coffee, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix cocoa, cinnamon and cloves with 1 cup flour.
Add 2 or 3 more cups of flour.
May be rolled or dropped.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with confectioners sugar frosting.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Mix the remaining ingredients separately.
Mix all ingredients together and stir. Pour on cookie sheet about 1-inch thick and bake for 1 hour at 225°, stirring occasionally.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt in a large bowl. Add salad oil and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese straws 1
directions: Grate cheese into large bowl and let stand at room temperature until softened.
Add softened margarine.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix salt, pepper and flour.
Gradually work into cheese/butter mixture. Blend until smooth.
Using a cookie press, squeeze out cheese straws onto ungreased baking sheets.
Cut into 2 to 3-inch lengths. Bake for about 15 to 20 minutes until crisp and golden.
Do not allow to brown.

title: easy chicken
directions: Mix together the rice and celery soup.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lay chicken pieces over rice mixture and sprinkle dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Add about 2 cups of water to help keep moist.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: rodeo bean bake
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in skillet; pour off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, seasoning mix and brown sugar; heat to boiling.
Combine with beans.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole or bean pot.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: new year's eve cake
directions: Bake chocolate mint cake as directed.
Prepare fluffy mint frosting; reserve 1/4 cup for decorating.
Fill and frost cake with remaining frosting.
Stir enough powdered sugar into reserved frosting until desired consistency for writing.
Place in decoration bag with writing tip.
Write # on patties.
Place patties in circle around top edge of cake.
Make hands of clock with chocolate chips.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: Rinse wings; pat dry with paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in shallow pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over wings.
Cover dish tightly with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven; pour all but about 1/4 of sauce into a bowl and reserve.
Baste wings with sauce in dish and broil 3 to 5 minutes or until wings are glazed a deep dark red.
Skim fat off reserved sauce and serve sauce with wings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll in party size balls.
Cook in oven 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 100.

title: diabetic colorful pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, combine the oil, vinegar, pepper, garlic, salt, oregano and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss well, cover and chill.
May wish to toss gently two more times while chilling and immediately before serving.

title: baked turnip casserole
directions: Cook turnips until tender, then drain and mash.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and crumble.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon drippings in pan and saute onions, garlic and pepper.
Stir in turnips and remaining ingredients except bacon and green onion. Spoon into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with bacon and green onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Combine chicken, cheese, beans, olives, salsa, chili powder and garlic in large mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Spoon into prepared dish; set aside.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, if frozen.
Drain and chop water chestnuts. Puree cottage cheese in food processor or beat very well.
Squeeze all the moisture from thawed spinach.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Chill minutes up to overnight.
Serve with fat free crackers or in a bread bowl.
Yields 8 servings (1/4 cup each). Has 80 calories, less than 1 gram of fat per serving.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, rice, raisins, sugar and salt in saucepan. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally until rice is tender, about 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Whisk egg, 2 tablespoons milk, nutmeg and cinnamon in small bowl.
Stir 1/2 cup rice into yolk mixture until blended, then stir into rest of rice.
Return to low heat and cook stirring, until most of liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm.

title: garlic mushrooms
directions: Cut stems from mushrooms; chop finely.
Mix chopped stems, onions, garlic and butter in 1-quart casserole.
Microwave uncovered on High until onions are crisp-tender, 2 to 3 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill mushroom caps with stuffing mixture.
Arrange mushrooms, filled sides up and smallest mushrooms in center of 10-inch pie plate.
Cover loosely and microwave 2 minutes.
Turn pie plate 1/2 turn.
Microwave until hot, 1 to 2 minutes.

title: cinnamon krispies
directions: Roll each slice; brush all sides with melted butter.
Roll in a cinnamon and sugar mixture and place in a cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: german corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the crackers.
Break crackers on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.
Serves 5.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine in large saucepan sugar and milk.
Bring to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto waxed paper.
This hardens fast.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons of milk and stir to get last of candy if it becomes too hard to spoon.
Makes 10 pounds candy.

title: cucumber potato salad
directions: In large bowl, place sliced potatoes and cucumber slices; stir together.
In smaller bowl, mix sour cream and sugar, then stir into potato-cucumber mixture.
Stir and dissolve 1/2 teaspoon sugar into vinegar; pour into and mix through the potatoes/cucumbers.

title: chocolate frosting glaze
directions: Bring butter, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and powdered sugar.
Beat with mixer and pour over baked cake.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Saute onions, green peppers and ginger in margarine.
Add salt.
Add sesame oil and chicken.
Cook until chicken browns. Add teriyaki sauce and sugar.
Simmer and stir for 10 minutes on low heat.
Serve with rice.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Add margarine while potatoes are hot.
Pout into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes and butter; place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and mix with corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate walnut bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift flour, blend into creamed butter mixture.
Butter a 2-quart small square Pyrex dish and press dough evenly over bottom.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over top.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Smooth melted chocolate evenly over top with back of spoon.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts and allow to cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 12 bars.

title: carrot cake
directions: Chop carrots, mix all ingredients together, ensure thoroughly blended.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Will make a stiff dough.
Roll into small balls and bake until done, 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: puffed rice
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients on medium heat.
Boil until bubbly and mixture turns light brown in color (about 10 minutes).
Add puffed rice.
If using unsalted peanuts, add with puffed rice.
(Turn heat off for electric stove.
Turn gas stove to low heat.)
Put in 9 x 12-inch buttered pan.
Press into shape of pan.
Careful!
It will be very hot! Work quickly!
Turn over on board and cut while still warm.
Cool before eating.

title: jackie's cream pralines
directions: In a large saucepan, put the sugar on medium heat for about 5 minutes until sugar starts to melt; stir constantly.

Add Pet milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for about 25 to 30 minutes. When mixture begins to thicken, add butter, pecans and vanilla. Test mixture in cold water to see if ready to spoon out onto greased area (counter or tabletop).
Need a large area.
Use tablespoon.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder and mix with sugar.
Stir in milk to make batter.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in 8 x 8 x 2-inch deep baking pan.
Pour batter over melted butter and do not stir. Pour 2 1/2 cups of your favorite fruit, mixed with 1 cup sugar over batter.
Bake 3/4 hour at 425°.
Serve either hot or cold.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown and drain ground beef; add all except cheese.
Let mixture come to boil.
Line casserole dish with tortilla chips, then layer of cheese and half of meat mixture, then another of chips, cheese and meat mixture.
Top with crumbled chips and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tossed salad(serves 100 people)
directions: *Approximately, depending on size.

title: dirt cake or flowerpot
directions: Line flowerpot with foil and cellophane.
Put half of cookies in bottom of pot and along sides.
Place mixture into pot.
Cover with rest of cookies.
Add gummy worms for accent.
Wrap base of flowerpot for decoration.

title: rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over the sugar, shortening and salt. Cool to lukewarm.

title: dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium bowl, combine apples, milk and cinnamon; set aside.
In a large bowl, cut 1/2 cup margarine into 1 cup of biscuit mix until crumbly.
Stir in apple mixture. Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.

title: jean's sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until done, peel and with mixer, beat until free of lumps.
Add remainder of ingredients and mix well. Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell; bake in preheated 425° oven for 5 minutes; then lower temperature to 325° and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: drop donuts
directions: Sift flour and salt. Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add Wesson oil and syrup in flour. Add yeast mixture. Cover let rise until double. Drop by spoonful into hot oil. When done cover with glaze of confectioners sugar and water.

title: yes you can make lasagna easily
directions: Add sauce and soup to browned ground beef.
Alternate layers of noodles, beef mixture, Mozzarella and cottage cheese.
Do this order 3 complete times.
Finish with a layer of Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl; add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread cream cheese frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake. Sprinkle with 1 cup pecans.
Yield:
One 9-inch layer cake.

title: ham and broccoli royale
directions: Cook rice following label directions; spoon into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook and drain broccoli; place over rice.
Melt butter in large frying pan.
Measure out 2 tablespoons and sprinkle over crumbs in a small bowl.
Saute onions in remaining butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk; continue to cook and stir until thick.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in ham; heat until bubbly. Pour over layers in pan.
Place cheese slices over ham layer; sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Cover and chill.
Forty-five minutes before serving, uncover and bake at 350° until browned.

title: apple cake(this recipe won an award of merit at the s.j.  county fair!)
directions: Combine apples with cinnamon and sugar (5 tablespoons).
Set aside while preparing batter.
In a large bowl combine all other ingredients.
Beat until well blended.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan. Pour in 1/2 of batter.
Place 1/2 of apples, layer over the batter. Add rest of batter, placing remaining apples on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool 20 minutes and remove from pan.

title: chicken squisito
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Season chicken with powders, salt and pepper. Heat oil in an oven-safe pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add chicken and saut

2 minutes on each side. Remove chicken. Saut onions in pan for 4 minutes. Add tomatoes and broth. Cook for 8 minutes to blend flavors. Place chicken in pan. Stir to combine. Mix cheeses together and sprinkle over chicken. Bake about 15 minutes. Serve with rice or pasta.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Cut sausage in pieces; brown in pot.
Saute onion until translucent.
After browning ingredients, place beans, catsup and sugar in same pot.
Cook slowly for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
A little more catsup or sugar may be added according to individual tastes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Add beaten egg white and water to nuts; stir until coated. Add sugar and spice.
Mix well.
Pour on a greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: mcneese's yeast rolls
directions: Heat buttermilk to lukewarm; take out 1/2 cup and add yeast. Mix sugar, salt, baking powder, oil and remainder of buttermilk in bowl.
Add yeast mixture, soda and flour and mix well.
Place on floured board and knead.
Roll out and shape as desired.
Allow 2 hours for rising.
Bake at 425° until rolls are golden brown. Yield:
4 dozen.

title: pistachio bundt cake
