directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate peanut butter candy
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together until creamy over low heat. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan lined with wax paper.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar, flour and 3 tablespoons juice.
Add cheese and pineapple to sugar and flour mixture.
Mix well.
Butter a 1-quart casserole dish. Pour in mixture.
Mix crackers and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: baked rice
directions: Place all ingredients in Corning dish and stir just to mix. Bake 1 hour on 350°.
Turn off oven.
Cover rice and let stay in oven 1/2 hour.
Mix with fork before serving.
This goes great with Pepper Steak.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix together egg, flour, butter, salt and onion.
Add cottage cheese and spinach.
Add Velveeta cubes.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Casserole may be frozen and thawed before baking.

title: fresh fruit bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Bake in 2 large or 3 small bread pans at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: fruit juice fizz
directions: Place ice in 4 water glasses.
Add 1/2 cup each juice and seltzer to each glass, stirring to blend.
Garnish with fresh fruit, if you wish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Save 1/2 of stuffing mix for top.
Melt margarine; add stuffing mix, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook squash until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients; top with remaining stuffing.
Cover and cook 45 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Chop nuts, dates and candy.
Combine with coconut.
Pour melted
butter
over
mixture;
let stand while preparing other mixture.
Beat
eggs, gradually adding sugar and other ingredients, mix well with nut mixture.
Bake in a greased tube pan or Bundt pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: a good hamburger
directions: Mix ground beef with ground pork.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/5 teaspoon pepper to ground meat.
Mix well.
Make 4 patties from ground meat.
Cover with foil and put back in refrigerator.
Mix mayonnaise, catsup, mustard, onions, pickles, garlic, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/5 teaspoon pepper.
Mix good in same bowl.
Put bowl in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours.
Also 4 large lettuce leaves and 2 sliced tomatoes.
Ready for cooking time, put 1, 2, 3 or 4 patties on grill or in frying pan; cook medium and turn until ready.
Melt butter and cover buns with it.
Brown buns on grill or in hot skillet until brown and hot.
Put lettuce on bun, add sauce on lettuce leaf, then hamburger, then tomato slice and sauce.
(It is ready to eat.)

title: olive sandwich spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on crackers or bread.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Press dinner rolls into 10-inch pan.
Spread with 2 teaspoons mustard.
Simmer 10 minutes in frying pan margarine, onions and zucchini.
Add parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder and oregano. Beat 2 eggs and mix with Mozzarella cheese.
Pour into shell and bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: make ahead meatballs
directions: In large bowl beat eggs and add next 5 ingredients.
Add beef and mix well.
Pat into a rectangle, score rectangle into 1 inch squares.
Form into balls and bake in a 400 degree oven for 10 to 15 minutes turning often.
Cool.
Place about 30 meatballs per batch.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter; add the next 6 ingredients and saute for 5 minutes.
Add undiluted chicken soup and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
This can be served on rice, noodles or toast.
Garnish with chopped chives.

title: kay's ratatouille rice
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add sauteed onions and garlic; cook and stir until tender (2 minutes).
Add rice, water, 2 teaspoons salt, pepper and basil.
Bring to a boil.
Cover tightly; simmer over low heat until liquid is absorbed (25 minutes).
Add vegetables and 2 teaspoons salt (or to taste).
Cover and cook until zucchini is tender, 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large casserole. Drizzle with 1 stick melted butter or oleo. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, butter and 1/4 cup powdered sugar thoroughly. Press evenly in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, making 1/2-inch edges.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato and banana casserole
directions: Mix all together except bananas.
Place half in casserole and spread bananas over this; then top with remaining sweet potato mixture.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil and vinegar and pour over drained beans.
Make the day before needed.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Spoon flour (not sifted) into dry measuring cup.
Level off and pour measured flour into bowl.
Add baking powder and salt to flour (not sifted).
Stir to blend.
Cream sugar, peanut butter, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate bits and peanuts.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mock wine punch
directions: Chill all liquids before mixing the first two.
At the last moment, add the Slice.
Yield:
enough for 25 servings.

title: "christmas yummy bars"
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients. Pour half into jelly roll pan. Refrigerate the other half; just keep in pan. Then combine butter, pudding and milk. On medium heat, boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add flavoring and powdered sugar. Pour slowly on top of chocolate layer. Freeze until hard. Add peanuts to remaining ingredients. Spread melted chocolate on top. Refrigerate until firm. Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: baked apples
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Spread evenly in pan.
Place peeled, cored and halved apples on top.
Cover tightly, simmer slowly until tender.
Serve with juice poured over and whipped cream on top.

title: fig loaf
directions: *If no sour milk, add 1 tablespoon vinegar to 1 cup milk.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough out onto 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 11 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Let crust cool.

title: low-fat muffins
directions: Stir just until mixed.
Add either pineapple (drained) or blueberries, apples (chopped) or cranberries.
Put sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 22 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.
Contains 110 calories and 3 fat grams.

title: campfire s'mores
directions: You will also need 1 well stoked campfire, several shaved long handled sticks and lots of people (a must).

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix with fingers and form balls size of large marble.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Place strawberries in container of an electric blender; process 30 seconds.
Add water and next 3 ingredients; blend until smooth.
Stir in ginger ale.
Serve over crushed ice.
Garnish, if desired.
Yields 4 cups.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Let cool in refrigerator.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Debone and cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix soups, broth, onion and Ro-Tel tomatoes together.
Crush Doritos and place in buttered casserole.
Layer chicken, soup mixture and 1/2 the cheese.
Repeat layers, but do not top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put remaining cheese on top and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well. Add eggs and stir until well blended, but do not beat.
Add lemon juice and corn meal.
Pour into pastry shell or 8 individual unbaked tart shells.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown (about 30 minutes).

title: refrigerator cucumber pickles
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Do not heat.
Pack jars with sliced cucumbers and onions.
Pour liquid over cucumbers and store in refrigerator.
Cure for 1 week before using.
(I use a gallon glass jar.)

title: baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake 3 hours at 300°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place berries in prebaked crust.
Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in a pan and cook until thick.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Pour over berries.
Chill until set.

title: peanut butter granola
directions: Toast the oats in the oven for 10 minutes at 350°.
Add the raisins, peanuts, sunflower seeds, powdered milk and wheat germ. Melt the peanut butter, oil, honey and salt over low heat.
Pour over other ingredients; stir.
Brown in oven in shallow pans at 325° for 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Mix Ricotta, sugar and eggs in a separate bowl.
Pour cake mix into a 9 x 13-inch floured and greased pan.
Then spread Ricotta mix on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on cake.
Very good.

title: cinnamon knots
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the milk, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Stir in yeast mixture, eggs and flour.
Let rise in a warm place for 1 hour or until doubled in size.
Stir down.
Pinch off dough about the size of a walnut and roll between hands until it's about 5 inches long.
Dip in melted Crisco, then in 1 cup of sugar and 3 tablespoons of cinnamon.
Tie into a knot and place into a greased muffin cup.
Continue until all dough has been used. Cover and let rise.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen rolls.

title: chess squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish to form crust.
Mix confectioners sugar (softened), 3 eggs and vanilla together.
Pour over crust and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 25 minutes or until top is light golden brown.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dice onion and green pepper; saute in pan in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano.
Precook hamburger and add to mixture.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook spaghetti noodles while mixture is simmering. Layer 1/2 spaghetti noodles in 9 x 13 pan.
Top with half hamburger mix, then sprinkle half the cheese on top of that. Repeat with spaghetti layer, hamburger mix and cheese.
Mix mushroom soup and water and pour over entire pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy boy's homemade rolls
directions: Melt shortening and add milk.
Dissolve and work in about enough flour to stiffness of biscuit dough.
Let rise 2 hours (double in size).
Flour board, pat down dough, work in a little flour, cut or make into rolls and turn over in greased pan.
Let rise about 1 hour more.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: trickem valley possum stew
directions: Thoroughly wash possum.
Debone; cut into 1 to 2-inch cubes. Heat large skillet; melt butter, garlic and 2 chopped onions in skillet.
Add possum cubes and saute all until possum is brown. Place peeled and chopped potatoes, carrots, onions, barbecue sauce and field peas into large boiler along with 3 quarts of water.
Add salt, pepper and other seasonings to taste.
Add sauteed ingredients.
Cook until all vegetables are done.
Serve immediately.
Do not retain leftovers.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes in a mold pan.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: salsa chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, mayo, cheese, green onions and salsa in small bowl, mix well.
Refrigerate for 30 min. to allow flavors to blend.

title: clam sauce(for spaghetti)
directions: Chop garlic and parsley together.
Combine oil and butter in skillet and heat.
Add clams, garlic and parsley and red and black pepper; stir.
(If using canned clams, add salt.)
Cook for 5 minutes.
(Start spaghetti water.)
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, 2 tablespoons clam juice and flour.
Cook for 20 minutes (simmer).

title: frozen blackberry pie
directions: Brush crust with 1 egg white.
Bake at 425° until lightly browned.
Cool completely.

title: chicken carolina
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Melt shortening in large deep skillet.
Brown chicken pieces, then remove from skillet.
Saute green pepper, onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in catsup and remaining ingredients.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover and simmer (basting occasionally) for 45 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve with hot fluffy rice, if desired.
Makes 6 servings, about 3 cups of sauce.

title: cornmeal-crusted fish
directions: The timing of the cooking will vary slightly, depending on the thickness of the fillets.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and strawberry jello; set aside.
In bottom of large cake pan (larger than 9 x 13-inch), cover bottom with marshmallows (not solidly).
Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour batter slowly over marshmallows.
Drop rhubarb mixture by spoonful over cake batter evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet basil salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in the blender and blend until smooth.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: I usually use the fresh broccoli.

title: karo lace cookies
directions: Mix flour and coconut.
Combine Karo, brown sugar and margarine in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; gradually blend in flour mixture, then vanilla.
Drop onto foil covered cookie sheet by scant teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool 3 to 4 minutes, until foil can be easily removed. Place cookies on rack covered with absorbent paper.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake for one hour at 350°.

title: pickled okra
directions: Sterilize jars and pack okra in tightly.
Put 1 clove of garlic and 1/4 teaspoon crushed red pepper to a jar.
Put water, vinegar, salt and dill seed in pan.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes, then pour over okra in jars.
Place jars in hot water and let sit until the tops seal.

title: pepperoni pasta
directions: Saute onion, garlic, green pepper, and pepperoni in oil in a skillet for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, oregano, and salt.
Cover and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and cook 1 minute to thicken.
Spoon sauce over spaghetti and sprinkle with parmesan cheese.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Microwave sugar, Karo and salt in 1 1/2-quart bowl, 4 minutes. Remove and stir in peanuts.
Return to microwave and cook 4 minutes.
Remove; add oleo and vanilla.
Stir well.
Return to microwave 2 minutes.
Remove and stir in soda.
Stir well and pour into buttered pan (I use cookie sheet).
Spread thin; cool.
Break into pieces.

title: heath bars
directions: Line a 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Place saltine crackers on top of foil.
Cook margarine and sugar for 3 minutes or until thickened.
Pour over crackers.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown at 350°.
Spread chocolate morsels on top of baked mixture as soon as you remove it from oven. Let stand 1 minute, then spread with knife.
When cool, put in refrigerator to harden.
Peel off foil and break into pieces.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Dice onion.
Mix in with ground beef in a skillet.
Brown and drain.
Peel and cut up potatoes; boil.
Mash potatoes and set aside.
Crumble beef cubes in 1/3 cup warm water.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add to ground beef and simmer about 15 minutes.
Transfer ground beef to 9-inch round pie dish or 6 x 9-inch rectangular dish.
Spread mashed potatoes on top with a fork (use back of fork to make crisscross lines across potatoes). Sprinkle cheese on top and brown under broiler oven.
For larger pie, double ingredients, using 9 x 13-inch oblong dish.

title: low-fat oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray or line 12 muffin cups.
Stir together oat bran, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In small bowl, whisk egg whites until frothy, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Add all at once to oat bran flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin cups.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: jogger's cocktail
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Run on high until smooth and well blended.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: snow balls(christmas favorite)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts. Mix thoroughly.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot and again when cool.

title: basic layer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour, eggs, vanilla and milk. Beat with mixer until smooth.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and done in the middle.
Makes 3 large layers or 4 medium layers.

title: coconut torte dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites, salt and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until very stiff peaks form and all sugar is dissolved.
Fold graham cracker mixture into egg white mixture. Spread into well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into wedges and top with scoops of vanilla ice cream.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until fork-tender.
Slice and lightly salt and layer in pan.
Add ingredients and cook until candied.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let stand overnight for flavors to blend.

title: pumpkin bread *(makes 3 loaves; great at thanksgiving)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in large bowl; make "well" in center and add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Portion batter into 3 loaf size pans (or about 6 small foil pans), that have been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour (or until it tests done), less time for small pans.
Cool slightly in pans, then place on rack to cool.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding mix and sugar; add milk.
Beat until thick.
Fold in whipped cream.
Layer graham cracker squares in bottom of pan. Pour half of filling on and smooth.
Add second layer of graham crackers and rest of filling.
Add another layer of graham crackers.

title: beans salad
directions: Cook green beans or heat, if canned.
Drain.
Let cool.
In a large bowl, combine cooled beans, kidney beans, pepper and onion. In a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine the vinegar, sugar, salad oil, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Shake well; discard garlic.
Pour over bean mixture; toss until well mixed.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: razor back corn bread
directions: In a deep 10-inch iron skillet, fry sausage until done (crumble).
Reserve 2 to 3 tablespoons drippings.
Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.

title: spaghetti sauce and meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients at one time; let come to a quick boil. Lower heat; let simmer for 2 hours.
Stir every now and then.

title: squirrel mulligan
directions: Cook meat
until tender and well done.	Add the vegetables and simmer
hour.
Season
to taste with black pepper, salt and Tabasco
sauce.
Sift
corn meal into mixture.
Stir and cook the meal.
Let	set
for a few minutes but keep warm and then serve.

title: mocha cream bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Stir in flour.
Divide batter in half.
Add nuts to half of batter and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chocolate to other half of batter and spread over first layer in pan.

title: summer squash supreme
directions: In a saucepan, cook sliced squash and onion in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots and fold in drained squash and onions.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into a log shape and wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: norwegian waffles
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour onto waffle iron.
Texture of cooked waffles is pliable and topping is optional as waffles are moist and rich.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Combine the first
ingredients
together.
Tear
the tortillas into quarters and lay
on
the bottom of a casserole dish sprayed with vegetable
spray.
Layer	the
meat mixture, onions and tortillas, finishing with the onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan cherry rounds
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line cookie sheets with foil; set aside.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix meat with egg, bread, catsup, oregano and garlic powder. Make meatballs.
Cook 15 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy peanut butter balls(kids cooking)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients, except wheat germ. Using your hands, form mixture into small balls about ping-pong ball size.
Spread wheat germ on a plate and roll each ball in it.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix the ingredients and place in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and add 1 cup more of Cheddar; sprinkle with paprika.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts.
Garnish with more green onions and bacon bits, if desired.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 2 layers.
Break 1 cake layer in small pieces in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix pudding with milk.
Put 1/2 of pudding on first layer of cake.
Slice 2 bananas on pudding, 1 can of pineapple, 1 can of pie filling and 1/2 of coconut.
Repeat all layers.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: white jello mold
directions: Mix gelatine and water in small pan.
Heat until dissolved and set aside.
Soften cream cheese; add sugar.
Beat well.
Add milk, vanilla and lemon juice to taste.
Add gelatine and fold in Cool Whip.
Spray mold with Pam.
Will set in 2 hours.
Decorate with fresh strawberries or peaches (canned).
Very good.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef strips in butter.
Remove from skillet.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid, and saute in drippings in skillet. Remove from skillet.
Into drippings, stir flour and soup mix. Gradually add water and mushroom liquid, blending well and stirring until thickened.
Return meat and mushrooms to skillet, cover and simmer, stirring from time to time, for about 20 minutes, or until meat is tender.
Blend in sour cream and serve over hot egg noodles or boiled potatoes.
Serves 6.

title: aunt mae's eggplant and onion ring batter
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Mix together the water, oil and milk.
Slowly add to the flour mixture.
Coat and fry vegetables in hot oil.

title: petite broccoli quiches
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and butter in a medium mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth. Add flour and beat at medium speed until smooth.
Shape pastry into 24 (1-inch) balls.
Place each ball into an ungreased miniature (1 3/4-inch) muffin pan.
Press dough onto bottom and sides to form shells.
Set aside.
Combine chopped broccoli and remaining ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well.
Spoon broccoli mixture evenly into shells.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until set and lightly browned.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: old-fashioned rich shortcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well and add egg.
Blend well; add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Turn into greased cake pan or heavy skillet (batter will be very stiff).
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Cool and split.
Spoon your favorite fruit or berries between layers and add whipped cream.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Then add vanilla and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix in M&M's.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Mix pumpkin (recipe on can).
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on pie filling.
Pour melted butter on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes until golden brown. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pie shell. Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Chill.
Yield: 1 pie.

title: chewy peanut butter strips
directions: Blend butter, peanut butter, sugar, salt, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients (which have been sifted together) to butter mixture; stir in coconut.
Spread in an 8 x 12-inch pan which has been rubbed with Crisco.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in strips while still warm and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: almond lace cookies
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Combine oats, sugar, flour, salt and baking powder. In separate bowl, whisk egg, butter and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients. Stir, then add almonds and mix well. Line a cookie sheet with foil (very important). Spray with cooking spray. Drop level teaspoons of dough 3-inches apart. Flatten slightly. Bake until golden, 9 to 10 minutes. Cool completely, then peel from foil.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Mix with electric beater until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pans 2/3 full and bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cinnamon peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In pie crust, add the pie filling. Combine sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Separate each biscuit into two sections. Dip each section in butter, then in sugar-cinnamon. Arrange on top of filling.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes, until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: turkey club pizza
directions: Roll dough out on pizza pan.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and bake until brown.
Cool.
Layer mayonnaise, basil, Swiss cheese, turkey, bacon and Monterey Jack cheese and top with tomatoes.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted well.

title: punch
directions: Mix together in gallon pitcher.

title: quail in french bread boats
directions: Sprinkle quail with salt and pepper and flour inside and out. Brown on all sides in butter in hot cast-iron pan.
Add water, mushrooms and flakes.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toast loaf bread on only one side. Add leaf of lettuce.
Spoon on salad.
Cut sandwich in half and serve.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in cocoa and powdered sugar.
Stir over low heat until blended.
Add vanilla.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Cut into squares.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy.
Sift flour; measure and add salt, soda and baking powder.
Sift again.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk; stir until smooth.
Chill dough.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick on floured board.
Cut and place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Put filling in center and seal with top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle onion and Tony Chachere on top.
Put melted butter on top.
Melt Cheez Whiz, sour cream and soup together.
Pour over top of potatoes.
Mix remaining melted butter with cornflakes and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix everything but chocolate chips and syrup.
Split batter in 1/2, put chips in one half and syrup in other 1/2.
Put chocolate chip mixture in a well greased bundt pan, layer syrup mixture on top and swirl.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli rice and cheese
directions: Mix and bake at 375° until done.
(If you like spicy, use jalapeno Cheez Whiz.)

title: mrs. nell beaty's ham
directions: You will need 1 roll heavy-duty foil.

title: walnut apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, toss sugar with flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Add apples and nuts to sugar mixture; toss gently to combine.
Set aside.

title: caramel coffee ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in small saucepan.
Coat bottom and sides of ungreased 12-cup fluted tube pan with 2 tablespoons of the melted margarine.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons of the nuts over bottom of prepared tube pan.
Add remaining nuts, brown sugar and water to remaining melted margarine.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits.
Cut each biscuit in half and shape into a ball. Place 20 balls in bottom of prepared tube pan.
Drizzle half of the caramel sauce over balls.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert immediately onto waxed paper and remove from pan.

title: blueberry pie filling to can
directions: Wash fresh blueberries.
Mix sugar and water and therm-flo until dissolved and then bring to boil.
Stir until thick and clear.
Add to berries and mix until berries are coated.
Put into pint or quart jars and can in hot, boiling water, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well mixed.
Pour into 2 buttered and floured 8 inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool and cover with icing (recipe to follow).

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pre-fry mushrooms until half done, then add sour cream, tomato paste, paprika and the garlic.
Cut meat across the grain in squares (approximately 1-inch).
Heat meat with butter and onion in skillet until meat is slightly brown.
Stir in flour; add sherry.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: napa cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage and onions and refrigerate.
Melt margarine in 9 x 15-inch baking pan.
Add crushed noodles, sesame seed and almonds.
Toss and toast until brown in 350° oven.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, then add carrots, apples, pecans, coconut and raisins. Combine and add to dry ingredients the eggs, vanilla and oil. Stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pan, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift together into bowl 2 tablespoons flour, 3/4 cup sugar, nutmeg and salt.
Add sour cream; beat well.
Add egg, and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add diced apples.
Place in pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° to 375° or until apples are done.
Remove from oven.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour, cinnamon and butter.
Sprinkle mix over top of pie and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion and green pepper. Drain.
Add Ragu sauce, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix noodles with hamburger and sauce mix.
Pour into long pan or dish. Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° until melted.

title: turtles
directions: Cover a pecan with 1/2 of a caramel.
Put in 300° oven for a few minutes to allow the caramel to melt.
Take out and put 1 square from a small Hershey bar on top.
Pop back in oven and let that melt.
Set out for a little while, eat and you will want another.

title: succotash
directions: Saute onions, green peppers and green onions. Add remaining ingredients. Cook in crock-pot on low all day until hot and bubbly.

title: caramel pudding cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture with milk.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in raisins.
Spread in greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Combine brown sugar and cold water; pour over batter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: windex
directions: Add a few drops of blueing, put in a quart can and fill with water.
Have sparkling clean windows!!

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until bubbly.

title: dipper's chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces on cutting board; set aside. Heat 3 inches of oil in large, heavy saucepan over medium-high heat until oil registers 375° on deep fry thermometer.
Adjust heat to maintain temperature.

title: zucchini blondies(may be doubled)
directions: Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Line pan with waxed paper.
Spray paper.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda in a small bowl.
Beat together butter and sugar in medium size bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat lightly. Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in zucchini, walnuts and half the chocolate chips.
Put rest of chips on top.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or until done.
Check after 30 minutes, if darkening too quickly.
Cover loosely with foil.
Cool in pan on rack.
When completely cool, loosen edges with knife; invert onto plate.
Remove waxed paper.
Invert again onto serving plate.
Cut into 16 (1-inch) squares.
Makes 16 servings at 206 calories per serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a medium saucepan combine brown sugar, cornstarch and water. Bring to a boil over medium heat; stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in peaches and lemon juice. Spoon mixture in 1-1/2 quart round baking dish. Heat oven to 350°.

title: baked beer burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine meat, pepper, Tabasco sauce, garlic, chili sauce, dry onion soup mix and 1/4 cup of the beer. Shape into 6 patties.
Bake at 400° until brown, about 10 minutes. Baste with remaining 1/4 cup of the beer.
Continue baking for an additional 10 to 15 minutes, until done.

title: english pea salad
directions: Layer lettuce, pepper, pickles, onion and peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar and spread over peas.
Add layer of eggs and layer of cheese.
Top with bacon bits.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: johnny cake
directions: Measure dry ingredients into small bowl and set aside. Measure the remaining ingredients into a blender and blend well. Then add cornmeal mixture.
Blend only until mixed, not a minute more.
Pour into buttered 8-inch pan or muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Mix the sugar, oleo and oatmeal together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt the chips and peanut butter over slightly cooled bars.
Spread.

title: apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches or 2 small ones).
Mix 1 cup sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Cream well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and the cinnamon. Sprinkle over the batter.
Bake until it tests done, 50 to 60 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan and thoroughly cool.
Store tightly covered.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add other ingredients.
Put into greased bowl or container, cover and refrigerate.
Take amount out as needed and roll out biscuits.
Bake in at least a 425° oven. Remaining dough will keep for several days.

title: nutty marshmallow bars
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Stir chopped peanuts, flour, oats, brown sugar, baking soda, salt and egg in a large bowl.
Stir in margarine with a fork until mixture is crumbly.
Press in an ungreased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 10 minutes.
Spoon Marshmallow Creme over hot layer.
Let stand 1 minute; spread evenly.
Drizzle topping over cream.
Sprinkle with 1 1/4 cups nuts.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Let stand until cool, then loosen edges from side of pan with knife.
Cut into bars with wet knife.

title: crab and corn soup
directions: Saute chopped onion and chopped green onion (tops and all) in margarine, until onions are soft.
Add corn and crabmeat.
Warm through.
Add half and half; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Serve.

title: porketta
directions: Cut deep slits in top & bottom of the roast.
Mix spices together and put a spoonful in each slit.
Cover loosely and bake in oven overnight at 200°.
Take roast out and pull meat apart with forks.
Add 1/2 cup water, cover and bake another 2 - 4 hours at 200°.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
Beat in the egg and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt and add to creamed mixture to make dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place in ungreased 1 1/2-inch muffin tins (or lined with papers).
Don't spread dough in cups.
Just sit ball in.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and immediately press in peanut butter cup in center until only top of peanut butter cup shows (one 10 ounce box cups).
Let cool in tins 10 to 15 minutes, then remove.
Freeze or store in airtight containers. Makes 40 cookies.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese. Simmer for 15 minutes. Ladle into bowls; top with grated cheese. Serve with Frito chips. Wonderful on a cold winter day!

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix cooked rice with cooked broccoli, cheese and soup.
Bake for at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jane's yum yum
directions: Pour fruit and juice in oblong pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on fruit.
Drizzle butter over top.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until top is golden brown.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine pineapple and marshmallows; let stand in refrigerator for several hours, then fold in Cool Whip or whipped cream. Refrigerate.

title: shipwreck noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Set aside.
Cook all other ingredients (but cheese) in skillet until done.
Put half cheese on top of noodles.
Top this with ground beef mixture, then cheese on top of this.
Pour can of cream of celery soup diluted witn 1/2 can water.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: couscous salad
directions: Whisk the first 3 ingredients in a small bowl; season with salt and pepper.
Place couscous in a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over; cover and let stand until water is absorbed, about 10 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Add shrimp, tomatoes, celery, green onions, mint and capers.
Mix in dressing.
Chill until cold, about 30 minutes, or up to 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken about 1 hour.
Cool and remove from the bone. Cut into bite-size pieces.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Add enough mayonnaise to coat well.

title: potato bake
directions: Follow package directions for potatoes except omit butter. Beat potatoes well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Grind orange with rind in grinder or blender; add oil, honey, milk and vanilla and blend.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to orange mixture.
Stir to blend.
Drop by large tablespoonfuls onto Teflon baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: aunt lydia's molasses bread
directions: Combine sugar, butter, molasses and eggs.
Add flour with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hearty vegetable and bean soup
directions: Sort and rinse beans; place in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water, 2-inches above beans; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Drain off water, reserving beans in Dutch oven. Add 1 1/2-quarts water and salt to beans.
Cover and simmer 3 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Transfer beans and liquid to container of an electric blender.
Cover and process until smooth. Set aside.

title: bread pudding
directions: *For sauce use Crowning Glory Sauce or Tennessee Whiskey Sauce found in this book.

title: spaghetti meat sauce for 4
directions: Brown ground beef in a small pan, stirring until it crumbles; drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, dried onion flakes, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and pepper.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cover, reduce heat, simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add spahgetti sauce and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain.
Spoon meat sauce over cooked spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.

title: samantha's brie potatoes
directions: Boil peeled garlic and potatoes together until done.
Mash potatoes and garlic together.
Melt Brie cheese and margarine together.
Add to potatoes and garlic.
Mix well.
Season to taste.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until it forms a hard ball in cold water (approximately 260° to 266° on thermometer). Beat egg whites until stiff. Pour syrup into egg whites and beat until stiff and it loses glossiness.
Divide evenly on 2 pieces of greased wax paper and spread about 1/4-inch thick, then spread with peanut butter.
Roll and let rest a short while before cutting.

title: "handed-down" chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add liquid.
Roll on floured board until paper thin.
Cut into smallest strips possible.
Drop into kettle of stewed chicken.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In cake pan dump pineapple and cherry pie filling; mix. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Cover.
Cut squares of butter and place on top of dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° until cake mix is brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: love cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift in flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cocoa alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into two greased and floured heart shaped cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Decorate with pink icing and border with chocolate candy kisses.
Yields 16 servings.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp.
Drain; reserve drippings. Crumble bacon.
Add onions and green pepper to drippings in skillet.
Saute until tender.
Stir in mushrooms, hominy, Worcestershire sauce, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes, over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in bacon. Alternate layers of hominy and cheese in 2-quart casserole, ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Tear cake.
Layer with cake, berries and Cool Whip.
(I use a glass dish or bowl for this.)
Keep 3 or 4 berries out for garnish on top with mint leaves, if you have them.

title: old-fashioned peanut butter
directions: Put all ingredients in electric blender.
Blend until it becomes paste-like or spreadable.
May need to add a little more oil.
Blend for several minutes.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: mom's corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar, oil and berries; put flour mixture to egg mixture. Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and let stand in refrigerator 6 to 8 hours.

title: luau beans
directions: Cook pepper, onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat.
Stir.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: deviled bean dip
directions: Blend soup into remaining ingredients just until smooth. Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Line medium-sized casserole dish with 6 tortillas.
Pour in meat mixture.
Cover with 6 tortillas.
Combine soup with milk.
Pour over top of casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 8.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray Pam in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put crushed potato chips on top, if desired. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray skillet with nonstick spray; drop mixture in skillet at medium-high heat.
Cook until brown on both sides.
(Before turning over remove skillet from heat and spray top so it will not stick when removing.)

title: cranberry pudding
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water.
Combine all ingredients; blend lightly.
Pour into a well buttered mold.
Cover; steam about 1 1/2 hours.
Unmold.
Serve with Butter Sauce.

title: artichoke supreme
directions: Mix all the ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch oil sprayed pan. Save some of the cheese to sprinkle on top of the mixture. Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.

title: black beans
directions: Wash beans well until water is clear; cover beans in a large pot with water.
Soak overnight.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with 1/4 to 1/2 cup salsa.
Evenly spread this mixture on tortillas, almost to the edge.
Roll up tightly.
Press to seal.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill in the fridge for 2 to 24 hours.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into oblong baking pan.
Place flank steak into marinade, turning to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.
Barbecue several minutes each side, center should be rare.
Slice thinly on the diagonal.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine ingredients (batter is loose) and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until top springs back to touch.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top of filling. Cube stick butter over cake mix.
Place pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apricot bars
directions: Mix 1/2 cup butter, sugar and 1 cup flour together well and press into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly brown at 350°.
Cool.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first five ingredients in saucepan.
Heat over medium-high heat until it comes to a rolling boil.
Cook 1 minute. Add peanut butter, then oatmeal.
Stir until peanut butter is melted and the mixture is well mixed.
Spoon onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: delectable dip
directions: You will need an extra large platter.

title: rice krispies marshmallow treat(cookies)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add marshmallows; cook over low heat until marshmallows are dissolved.
Add Rice Krispies and stir; press into well-greased pan.
Cut into squares.
Yields 24 squares.

title: "ali's black bottom cupcakes"
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat together cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Add 6 ounces semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Set aside.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion and cauliflower.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle cheese on mayonnaise.
Sprinkle bacon on top of cheese.
Refrigerate if made ahead.
Toss just before you eat.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Wet chicken slightly.
Dip in bread crumbs with paprika.
Put in oven in a greased pan for 50 minutes. Take out.
Brush with melted butter and put back in for 10 minutes more.

title: pineapple and cream cake
directions: Bake cake in large pan.
Mix milk with softened cream cheese, add pudding contents until thick.
Spread on cooled cake.
Put fruit on top of cream cheese mixture.
Whip heavy cream.
Add sweetener to taste, spread on cake.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: butter pecan angel pie
directions: Blend flour, margarine and pecans.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and cool thoroughly.
Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and small container Cool Whip.
Spread this on crust.
Mix butter pecan pudding mix with cold milk.
Spread over cream cheese, etc. layer.
Top with large carton Cool Whip.

title: frozen caramel pies
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk until smooth. Stir in cool Whip. Spread 1/2 the mixture in the 3 pie crusts. Sprinkle with 1/2 the nuts and coconut. Drizzle on caramel. Spread with rest of cream mixture, sprinkle with nuts and coconut. Drizzle with caramel and freeze.

title: applesauce oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix well.
Place by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Shake bag with sugar and cinnamon. Layer in a greased tube pan.
Sprinkle nuts between layers.
Melt brown sugar and margarine, pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and then serve.

title: sausage, biscuits and gravy
directions: Cut sausage roll into 1/2-inch patties.
Lightly brown sausage in skillet on one side.
Remove patties; drain fat.
Return sausage to pan and brown other side.
Remove patties from pan, leaving drippings in pan.
Add flour to pan and brown in the drippings, stirring until tan colored.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/4 cup of milk, mixing to make paste.
Return to stove and add remaining milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickens.
Season with a little salt and lots of pepper.
Return patties to gravy and cook 10 minutes longer and serve over biscuits ("homemade or whatever"). I prefer Grands because they are larger than most!

title: cube steak
directions: Brown steak on both sides in oil.
Brown onion.
Then add water, sugar, caraway seed, onion and steak together.
Simmer until steak is done.

title: charleston she-crab soup
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler and blend in flour until smooth.
Add the milk, then the cream very slowly.
To this add the mace, celery salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add the crab meat and fold gently.
Test for additional salt and pepper.
Warm sherry in a pitcher.
Add sherry to taste in each bowl.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana-nut chip bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat bananas, sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla. Combine the dry ingredients; stir into banana mixture.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into two greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Drain the oranges and pineapple.
Slice onion thin.
Combine chicken, celery, oranges, pineapple and nuts.
Chill thoroughly. Blend together yogurt, salt and marjoram.
Add chicken mixture. Toss together lightly to coat all ingredients.

title: soup
directions: I cook it in the microwave.
Then eat it.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: In
3-quart
saucepan,	stir Pet milk, marshmallows and orange juice
over
low
heat
until marshmallows are melted. Remove from
heat.
Stir
in dates, raisins, walnuts, candied fruit
and candied
cherries.	Stir until well blended graham cracker crumbs and spices (spices may be omitted, if desired). Press firmly into 5 or 6-cup ring mold or loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Cover tightly
and
chill
for 2 days.
Makes a 3 pound cake.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain.
In blender, mix milk, egg, cheese, butter, onion, salt and caraway seed.
Pour over spinach in 9 x 13-inch or 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garden vegetable dip(recipe for calorie counters)
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cottage cheese and milk until creamy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour. Serve with crisp cold relishes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In 2 qt. casserole, combine onion and butter.
Microwave on HIGH for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until onion is tender, stirring once.

title: melt-a-way casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender. Melt the 1/4 cup butter and add onions, cook over low heat about 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in flour, salt, pepper and thyme. Gradually add milk and cook stirring constantly until thickened. Arrange half of macaroni in lightly greased 2 quart baking dish. Layer half the meat over macaroni. Put cheese on top and repeat layers. Pour thickened sauce over all. Combine crumbs, 2 Tbsp. butter and parsley. Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to the instructions.
While still warm, poke holes on the top of the cake.
Pour milk and butterscotch topping over the top.
Let completely cool in the refrigerator.
When cold, spread cool whip over the cake then sprinkle Heath bars over the top.
Store in the refrigerator at all times until all gone.

title: heavenly biscuits
directions: Mix flour and mayonnaise.
Add milk.
Drop into well-greased muffin tins.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 to 9 biscuits.

title: rippled coffee cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, sour cream, eggs and oil. Pour in sprayed cake pan. Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon and swirl through cake batter. Bake cake at 350° until cake tester comes out clean. Mix milk, vanilla and powdered sugar and pour over cake.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over hamburger buns.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk.
Add Cool Whip, oranges and pineapple.
Crush 3/4 package cookies and add to mixture.
Top with remaining cookies.
Refrigerate.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Wash chicken and put in 10-quart kettle about 3/4 full of water.
Add celery and onion; boil slowly until scum forms and skim off the scum.
Let boil slowly until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and let cool; debone and remove skin; set aside.

title: mississippi southern pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix in large bowl the sugar, oil (canola), Karo syrup, eggs (beaten), vanilla and pecans. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake for 30 minutes. Turn off oven and leave pie in for another 45 to 55 minutes or until set and fairly dry.

title: italian beef(made with venison)
directions: Place roast on top of stove and cover with water.
Let boil. Place bouillon cubes in pot and boil approximately 3 hours or until tender.
Pull all meat off bone and shred.
Place meat back into broth mixture and add Italian seasonings, fennel seasonings, pepper and pepper juice.
Cook for 1 hour more or until broth is barely over the meat.
Extra water may be needed during boiling.

title: chocolate coconut bars
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler over hot water.
Add chocolate morsels; stir until melted, then remove from heat.
Let cool.
Add marshmallows; stir lightly.
Spread half of the coconut in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread chocolate mixture over coconut in pan. Top with remaining coconut.
Press down with a spoon.
Refrigerate until set.
When well chilled, cut into small squares.

title: aunt bill's microwave candy
directions: Combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and butter.
Cover with plastic wrap; punch holes in wrap.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes. Stir and turn dish.
Continue cooking for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Return to oven for 2 minutes or until soft ball forms in cold water or it shows 236° on a candy thermometer.
(Do not put candy thermometer in microwave.)
Add vanilla and beat with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Watch closely.
Stir in pecans and spread in a buttered dish (12 x 7-inch).
Cool; cut into pieces.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix well all the ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
(Makes own crust.)

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add beaten egg.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix quickly.
Put in muffin tins.
Serve while hot with butter and molasses.
Delicious!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and simmer about 1 hour.
Will refrigerate good for several days.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies; set aside.
In large bowl, blend (low speed) Cool Whip, pudding and milk; mix well.
In small bowl, mix cream cheese, softened butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Mix both bowls together.

title: wassail(spiced cider)
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer over low heat.

title: copper pennies (carrots)
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients for sauce.
Arrange carrots, pepper and onion in large layers in pan.
Pour sauce over vegetables. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: orange date cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add all-purpose flour in 3 parts alternately with buttermilk.
Add orange rind, dates and pecan pieces.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a preheated 325° oven.
When cake is done, pour sauce for Orange Date Cake over it and allow cake to cool in pan.

title: crawfish pilaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, place in rice cooker and cook until cooker "bings."
Stir and let stand an additional 10 minutes.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Prepare lime Jell-O as directed on package.
Pour into a long, clear 2 quart glass dish and let set in refrigerator.
Bring water to a boil and add lemon Jell-O and dissolve.
Add marshmallows and let melt. Add cream cheese; stir until smooth and remove from heat.
Add pineapple and evaporated milk.
Pour over the "set" lime Jell-O and chill.
Prepare cherry Jell-O; pour over pineapple layer and let set.
Cut into squares after last layer sets.

title: classic chess pie
directions: Unfold pie crusts, and stack on a lightly floured surface. Roll into 12 inch circle.
Fit pie crust into a 9 inch pie place according to package directions; fold edges under, and crimp.
Line pie crust with aluminum foil, and fill crust with pie weights or dried beans.
Bake at 425° for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove weights and foil; bake 2 to 3 more minutes or until golden.
Let cool completely.
Stir together sugar and next seven ingredients until blended.
Add eggs, stirring well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50-55 minutes, shielding edges of pie with aluminum foil after 10 minutes to prevent excessive browning.
Cool pie completely on a wire rack.
Preparation time:
23 minutes.
Bake 1 hour and 3 minutes.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Bring to a full boil the sugar and syrup.
Remove from fire and add peanut butter.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over cornflakes (not crushed) and mix gently.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Eat!

title: chicken dressing
directions: Saute chopped pepper, onion and celery in margarine.
Debone chicken (save broth) in a large roaster.
Pour chicken broth over the cornbread and rice until moist.
Let set for a few minutes so the cornbread can soak up the broth.
Add margarine.
Add more broth if it needs it.
Add deboned chicken, chopped eggs, sauteed vegetables and green onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° until it gets good and brown.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs and set aside.
Pour cake mix, pudding mix and poppy seed into a bowl.
Add oil and hot water; mix well.
Then pour in beaten eggs.
Mix well.

title: bread stuffing
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter for about 10 minutes, until tender.
Add the cooked vegetables and seasonings to the bread cubes; mix thoroughly.
If dressing seems dry, add 2 tablespoons water, milk or fish stock to moisten.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add enough milk to wet ingredients.
Then add rest of milk and cook until thickened. Cool.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in small amount of butter.
Combine all ingredients except cheese and garlic croutons.
Stir in a large bowl and pour into buttered ramekins.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until mixture bubbles, then at 250° for 15 minutes.
Top with garlic croutons and serve immediately.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Warm string beans and soup together.
Put in casserole dish. Top with cheese and bake until cheese is soft and top with Durkee onion rings; brown.

title: sweet-sour spareribs
directions: Spread ribs, meaty side up, in single layer in a large shallow pan and brown in oven at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain off fat. Combine all remaining ingredients, except salt and pepper, in a saucepan.
Stir smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thick and glossy, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over browned meat.
Spoon sweet-sour sauce over each piece and use half the sauce.
Reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake 45 minutes.
Cover meat with foil for part of cooking time.
Turn ribs; cover with remaining sauce and bake for 30 minutes more or until well done. Total cooking time is about 2 hours.

title: cowboy pork chops and pinto beans
directions: Combine 1 teaspoon cumin, salsa, barbecue sauce, onions and pinto beans. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Set aside and keep warm. Combine remaining 1 teaspoon cumin, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Sprinkle over both sides of chops. Place chops on broiler pan coated with cooking spray. Broil 5 minutes on each side or until done. Serve with beans.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Blend ingredients until well blended.
(May lightly warm in microwave to softened consistency.)
Refrigerate before serving.

title: coconut supreme pie
directions: Mix ingredients and
cook
for 15 minutes at 400°, then lower temperature to 325° for 35 minutes.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Clean raspberries.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water to sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thick. Add jello.
Blend in the clean berries last.
Pour in prepared and baked pie shell.
Cool and serve with whipped cream.

title: mother's missouri style hush puppies
directions: Preheat fat to 375°.
Make well in the center of dry ingredients.
Add liquid mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Form into small cakes (1 tablespoon each).
Deep fry one layer deep 3 to 4 minutes or until well browned.
Turn with tongs when crispy on surface.
Drain.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: blake's ducky plucky bread
directions: Cut biscuits in 1/4.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Coat biscuits well with mixture.
Place in a tube pan. Add 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pull off in bite sizes.
Can be mixed the night before.
Refrigerate and bake the next morning.

title: easy salmon croquettes
directions: Cook potato and mash with tablespoon of butter.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Shape into croquettes and roll in some cracker crumbs.
Fry in oil in skillet or deep fry until brown.

title: date oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, salt, soda and spices; sift twice.
Cream the fat, gradually add sugar and cream until light and fluffy.
Add the beaten eggs to the creamed mixture and stir in the oats and milk.
Sift the flour over the dates, coconut and nuts.
Mix well.
Stir into the oatmeal mixture.
Mix in thoroughly.
Drop by small tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets, 3-inches apart.
Bake in 350° oven for about 10 or 12 minutes or until delicately browned.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: microwave nutty corn
directions: Note:
Use any nuts you wish, pecan or walnut halves, almonds, salted peanuts or any nutty combination.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Line casserole dish with broccoli.
Combine soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle on bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: linguini salad
directions: Place cooked linguini in
a large bowl.
Mix all other ingredients with it using as much seasoning, olives, pepper and onions as you want.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Shred beef in blender.
Save 1/2 cup shredded beef.
Blend cream cheese, onion, remaining beef, Worcestershire sauce, Accent and Tabasco.
Shape into 2 large or 4 small balls.
Roll in reserved shredded beef.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.

title: lime water chips
directions: Slice cucumbers 1/4-inch thick.
Cover with water and lime. Let stand 24 hours.
Rinse well and let stand in clear water for 3 hours.
Drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour cold solution over pickles.
Let stand overnight.
Simmer 30 minutes; put in jars and seal.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together - pour into oval baking dish. Cover with foil, poked with
holes.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Check ovens, they vary.
Knife should be a little wet when checking souffle for doneness.

title: munchies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour over crackers.
Shake or stir to coat crackers.
Bake at 200° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
To store seal in a bowl.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Mix sour cream, onion salt and bacon together.
Spread on rolls and roll up.
Place on baking sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: ferne plumlee's fancy apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, toss sliced apples in sugar, cinnamon, lemon juice and melted margarine making sure each apple slice is coated with mixture. Let set for a few minutes.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Melt butter; stir in cocoa.
Add eggs, sugar, flour and salt. Mix well.
Pour into greased 11 x 14-inch pan or 2 (8-inch) round pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When done, put marshmallows on top.
Return to oven to melt.
Cool.

title: squaw bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and stir.
Roll out on floured wax paper, cut in squares and fry in deep hot skillet of Crisco until golden brown.
Serve hot with honey.

title: far east tuna munchies
directions: Combine ingredients in a small bowl.
Spread 1/2 of the mixture on 12 crackers.
Arrange on paper plate.
Microwave on High for 60 seconds rotating plate after 20 seconds.
Repeat with remaining mixture and crackers.

title: scottish griddle scones
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Pour in milk and melted margarine, enough only to make soft but not sticky dough.
Turn out on to floured surface and knead a few times.
Divide into 4 portions.
Roll each ball out to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness.
Place on heated griddle at medium heat.
Turn when golden brown on bottom and brown second side.
Keeps well and can be toasted.

title: easy potato rolls
directions: In a small bowl, cream sugar and Crisco, add potatoes, salt and eggs.
Beat in yeast, 2 cups flour and remaining water.
Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Form into a ball, place in a large greased bowl and grease top of dough.
Cover and let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down.
Pinch off small pieces to form 1 inch balls.
Place 3 in each greased muffin cups.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes then brush with melted butter.
Remove from pans to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 36 to 45.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Cook and peel shrimp.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours. (This works well sealed in a 2-gallon Ziploc bag.)
Stir occasionally to insure all shrimp are well coated.
Before serving, pour shrimp into a colander to drain marinade, but do not rinse shrimp.
Leftover shrimp can be stored in refrigerator for up to 3 days (but you won't have any left!).

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased
pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: surf and turf
directions: Slash fat every 2 inches on edges of steak.
Place on broiler pan or grill about 2 inches from heat.
Cook 5 minutes each side for rare, 6 minutes each for medium or 7 minutes each for well done.
Season with salt and pepper after cooking.
Drop lobster into pot of boiling water.
Bring water back to boiling.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook tails completely.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream Crisco and margarine until light.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy. At low speed, add half of flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in the rest of the flour with hands.
Add nuts.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix with the creamed shortening.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake until lightly browned but still soft.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out with crinkled tops.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Coat 9-inch iron skillet with oil. Combine meal, flour, soda, baking powder and egg and mix well. Add buttermilk to make consistency of cake batter.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Add onion, corn, rice, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Mix well. Slice tops from peppers; discard seed.
Spoon ground beef mixture into peppers.
Place in a baking dish.
Top with a slice of Velveeta cheese.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 50 minutes.
Yield: 5 servings.

title: easy rotelle and mushrooms
directions: Saute onion and garlic until tender, but not brown.
Add mushrooms, water and bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in cooked rotelle.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rotelle is tender.
Stir in parsley, salt and pepper. Serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Blanch broccoli.
Put ingredients in layers in casserole with onions on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not cover.

title: a quickie meal
directions: Put small amount of oil in frypan and add all other ingredients.
Add 1 cup of water.
Keep adding water in small amounts and keep covered.
Cook until potatoes and carrots are done, about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: stew
directions: Brown hamburger until it is no longer pink.
Add cut up vegetables, peas, seasonings, soup and water.
Bake in 350° oven or on top of stove until vegetables are tender.
Stir as needed.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to simmer. Strain and serve hot.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add next 3 ingredients, folding in Cool Whip last with a spoon.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze overnight.
Set out 1 hour before you serve.

title: tuna broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 450° (hot).
Cook broccoli stalks 3 minutes and drain.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover with tuna.
Mix soup and milk, pour over tuna.
Sprinkle potato chips over top. Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: vincent price's broiled garlic chicken
directions: Sprinkle or rub chicken with a paste of olive oil and garlic. Sprinkle with pepper.
Broil about 5 minutes per side.
Put into a covered casserole.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes, until tender.

title: candy apple walnut pie
directions: In large bowl, toss together apples, walnuts, cinnamon candies, 1/3 cup sugar and flour.
Pour into one frozen pie crust. Break or crumble second frozen crust into very small pieces; toss with remaining 2 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in preheated 375° oven on a preheated baking sheet 55 to 60 minutes or until candies melt and bubble up through crumbled crust.
Cool completely before serving.
Serves 8.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine above ingredients and mix.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 1 cup.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute ground beef until gray in color.
Add onion and cook only until warm through.
Add soups, milk, enchilada sauce, chopped peppers and cheese.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until dough is fine granules.
Add milk; stir with fork, then knead dough with floured hands.
Roll dough to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out shapes. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: welsh cakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Add shortening and margarine, mix until like coarse meal.
Add raisins.
Beat eggs with milk, add to flour mixture to make a dough.
Roll at 1/4-inch thick on floured board and cut with glass. Makes about 30 cakes.
Cook at 350° on electric grill or on top of stove in thick skillet.

title: grandmother's sour cream cake
directions: Sift flour.
Blend with soda.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Stir in sour cream; add flour and soda to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in.
Bake in large, greased and floured pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Does not need frosting.

title: (easy) texas millionaires
directions: Melt caramel candy, water and butter in double boiler.
Mix in nut halves and drop by tablespoonfuls on buttered tray to cool. Mix in double boiler chocolate bar and paraffin wax.
Mix until chocolate and wax are melted.
Dip cooled candy drops and place on waxed paper.

title: potluck favorite grits and cheese(1977 cookbook)
directions: Stir
boiling
water,
grits and salt together and cook until smooth and thick.
Stir cut up cheese and margarine into cooked grits
until
melted.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinated rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Cool.
Chop all ingredients small.
Mix all together with rice.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve at room temperature.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix until thick and pour over cream cheese mixture.

title: tamale squares
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk and margarine; beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper; cook until tender.
Reserve 1/3 cup cheese spread and 1/2 cup tomato.
Stir in remaining cheese, tomato and chili powder.
Spoon meat mixture over batter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with reserved cheese spread and tomato; continue baking 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: On 1 pie crust for bottom crust, put potatoes with juice, sugar, butter and vanilla in pan.
Mix flour and milk together until well blended.
Pour over other ingredients.
Put pie crust on top.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit, coconut and nuts together in large bowl.
Add sour cream and then marshmallows.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: black bean soup
directions: Pick over beans well and wash and drain.
Cover with 4 inches of water and soak overnight.
Drain beans; discard water.
Rinse with fresh water.
Cook beans in 6 cups of cold water; bring to boil, partially covered, stirring occasionally.
Simmer 2 to 4 hours until tender.
After 1 hour of cooking, add onion, carrot, diced ham, lemon juice, red pepper, salt and black pepper, garlic and white wine; also more water if necessary.
When done, take out part of mixture and puree.
Put back into pot.
Add sherry. Sprinkle chopped egg on soup when served.

title: icebox christmas cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts. Shape each into 1 1/2-inch rolls and freeze.
When ready to bake, cut into 1/2 slices.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Stir in brown sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil hard for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk. Return saucepan to heat.
Bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat. Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in sugar, beating until smooth.
Pour over pound cake.

title: cheesy ham and broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, combine potato slices and 3 cups boiling water; let it stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add ham, onion and broccoli; blend well.
Spoon into greased baking dish.

title: stuffed bread dip
directions: Shell out center of one loaf of bread for dip and break apart second
for
dipping.
Mix
sour
cream, mayonnaise and spices. Break
apart
chopped corned beef and mix with canned corned beef. Fill into loaf and surround with pieces to dip.

title: poulet de normandie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Put half on bottom of a 12 x 8-inch casserole that has been greased.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Put over bread mixture in casserole.
Cover with other half of bread mixture.
Beat together 2 eggs and 1 1/2 cups evaporated milk.
Pour over casserole and cover with foil. Refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking.
Spread 1 can mushroom soup over top; thin a little to help spread.
Bake, uncovered, 40 minutes at 325°.
Top with sharp grated cheese. Return to oven 10 minutes.

title: baked curried cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Break cauliflower into flowerets. Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Drain.
In 2-quart casserole, stir soup, cheese, mayonnaise and curry powder together.
Add cauliflower and mix well.
Toss bread crumbs in melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: dutch slaw
directions: Mix together all the ingredients and put them in a glass jar. Put on the lid and refrigerate it until needed.
This salad will last a long time if kept refrigerated.
Recipe taken from the "Amish Cookbook."

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake layers.
Cool completely.
Prepare instant pudding according to directions.
(Refrigerate to set up.)
Place 1 cake layer in bottom of 6-quart punch bowl.
Add in layers 1/2 of each ingredient in following order; prepared pudding, cherry pie filling, fruit cocktail, pineapple, nuts, coconut, Cool Whip.
Add 2nd layer and continue in same order using remaining ingredients. Garnish top with cherries, nuts and more coconut.
Refrigerate. Serves 35 people.

title: old fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Cook pasta according to directions on package. In saucepan over low heat, melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper. Cook 1 minute. Gradually add milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sauce thickens. Add cheese; stir until melted. Stir in pasta. Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: coconut zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients with oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add zucchini, coconut and nuts last.
Bake at 350° until brown and top springs back.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: crock-pot cube steak
directions: If using round steak, cut in serving size pieces and pound with cube mallet.
Brown in skillet, to which enough Crisco has been added to keep it from sticking.
When browned, put in the crock-pot.
Put the soup in the skillet in which the meat was browned.
Heat until fryings from bottom of skillet have loosened. Add minced onion to soup.
Pour over the meat in the crock-pot; be sure to get a little of the soup under the meat in the crock-pot. Cook for approximately 3 hours.
(Can also use ground beef formed into patties and follow same directions.)

title: truffles
directions: Preheat oven; check to be sure there are no rubber balls or plastic soldiers lurking on the shelves.
Remove blocks and toy autos from table.
Grease pan.
Crack nuts.
Measure 2 cups flour; remove Johnny's hands from flour and off him.
Remeasure flour. Crack nuts to replace those Johnny knocked on the floor.
Get another bowl.
Answer doorbell.

title: old english cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pat down.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator.
