Roll in nuts, parsley or chives.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test with knife.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: applesauce pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix the milk, eggs, cream cheese, food coloring and lime juice together.
Pour into the pie crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Chill and serve.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a slow cooker.
Cook on medium heat while you're at work (6 to 8 hours).
Dinner is ready when you get home.
(Make sure you remove the bay leaf.)

title: ham and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In saucepan melt 1/4 cup butter, blend flour, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in macaroni, ham and apple slices.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter, add bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes, or microwave at full power for 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar in a large mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Stir in hot water.
Combine dry ingredients.
Blend into sugar mixture.
Stir in grated potato, pecans and vanilla, blending thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Spoon mixture into three 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool on wire racks.
Spread Coconut Filling between layers and on top of cake.
Yields three 8-inch layers.

title: amazing chicken and dressing
directions: Bring broth to a rolling boil.
Rub flour on both sides of the tortillas, using all of the flour.
Cut tortillas into 1 1/2-inch strips.
Drop in boiling broth.
Reduce heat and simmer in a covered pot.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in chicken and milk until heated throughout.
Let stand off heat 10 minutes, covered. Serves 4; 1 bread, 1 1/2 protein, 37 optional calories.

title: cranberry pecan bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Make a well in the center. Combine next 4 ingredients.
Pour into well and stir just until moistened.
Fold in last 3 ingredients.

title: yummy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream
sugars
and
butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Mix
oats,
flours, spices, soda and salt.
Add raisins and
pecans
to oats and flour mixture.
Add to butter mixture a little at a time until well blended.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Remove with spatula onto paper
towel to	cool.
Bake
at
for
10 to 15 minutes. Yield: 4 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar.
Add 7-Up.
Bring to a boil.
When liquid begins to thicken and clear, add strawberry jello.
Cook until slightly thick.
Allow liquid to cool.
Gently fold in strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Top with whipped topping.

title: crazy pie
directions: Put all in blender, counting to 10. Pour into greased 9 inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Adjust ingredients to taste.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: The night before, cut marshmallows into fourths and mix with pineapple and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover tightly.

title: chicken scallop
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions on package for dry stuffing.
Spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with layer of chicken.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add cool broth and cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into eggs (be careful not to curdle) and return to hot mixture.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes to set.
Cut in squares and serve with Sauce.

title: cherry delight
directions: Roll crackers very fine.
Mix sugar and softened margarine and bake in an oblong dish for about 10 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over crust. Add nuts (optional), then Dream Whip and pie filling.

title: easy pumpkin swirl
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Line with wax paper and grease wax paper.
Set aside.

title: spicy carrots
directions: Place carrots, sugar, salt and cinnamon in 1-quart casserole. Toss to combine.
Dot with butter.
Cover tightly.
Microwave 7 to 8 minutes on High or until carrots are tender-crisp.
Yields 4 servings.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Drain fat and add 15 ounces tomato sauce; simmer.
Cook noodles. When noodles are done, drain well.
Stir in sour cream and cream cheese.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until well browned.
Remove sausage with slotted spoon to paper towel and let drain.
Spread margarine on pie crust.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese on pie crust. Preheat oven to 425°.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix strawberries and grapefruit juice.
Pour over ice. Add ginger ale.
Serves 25.

title: baked stew
directions: Grease dish.
Pour tomato soup and water over mixture.
Add a bay leaf.
Season and stir.
Cover with foil and bake for 5 hours at 275°.

title: baked chow mein
directions: Brown meat and mix all together.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in medium oven.
Serves 12.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and refrigerate for at least an hour.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix hamburger, beans, soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
Put in pie crust.
Top with potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together all ingredients and pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake 60 minutes.
Let cool approximately 30 minutes and invert onto a plate.
Sift on confectioners sugar and serve.

title: noodle strudel
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients with noodles.
Put into a large 9 x 13-inch greased pan and sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set before cutting.

title: chicken casserole oriental
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onion until clear (don't brown).
Stir in green pepper, celery, chicken broth and soy sauce.
Blend well.
Add chicken, mushrooms and chestnuts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together. Cook over low heat until thick, approximately 5 to 10 minutes.

title: red snapper mykonos
directions: Preheat broiler for 15 minutes to 425°.
Clean and wash fish; remove membrane.
Dry thoroughly with paper towels.
Line a roasting pan with heavy-duty foil and place fish on it.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Chop cauliflower. Drain and wash shrimp. Add to cauliflower. Mix in Miracle Whip.
Add dill weed to taste, about 2 tablespoons. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Good to make ahead for outings.

title: cabbage and sausage
directions: Combine.
Cover and cook over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes or until cabbage and onions are soft and translucent.
Serve.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper, then drain.
Add sauce.
Boil spaghetti and drain well.
Blend cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream together.

title: minty chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Combine chocolate and cream in saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring just until chocolate is melted.
Sauce should be smooth.
Add sugar and cook, stirring constantly until completely dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and flavoring. Transfer to covered containers and store in refrigerator.
Will keep for up to 2 weeks.
Makes 2 cups.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add to cereal in large bowl.
Mix wet ingredients; add to large bowl.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes. Will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks!

title: carrot cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato candy
directions: Add vanilla and salt to mashed potatoes.
Chill.
Add powdered sugar slowly to potatoes until stiff and dry.
Divide mixture into 3 parts.
On waxed paper, roll out 1/4-inch thick, about 4 x 12-inches.
Spread dough with thin layer of peanut butter.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Repeat other 2 parts.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill several hours.
Slice.
Store in refrigerator until all is eaten.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Add flour until dough is stiff enough to roll. Roll and cut out cookies. Bake at 350 degrees for 8-10 minutes. Ice when cooled.

title: meatball soup
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, chopped potato, onion, milk, 1 tablespoon parsley and salt.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch meatballs.
Cook in oil in Dutch oven until light brown.
Remove meatballs; drain fat from Dutch oven.
Mix tomatoes (with liquid) and remaining ingredients in Dutch oven, breaking up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add meatballs; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Bring this to a boil.
Pour over top of biscuits and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes to cool before removing.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruits; mix all together.
Let stand in refrigerator 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: homemade frozen sherbet
directions: Combine and mix well. Pour into ice cream freezer and finish filling with plain milk to fill line. Stir well and freeze.

title: low calorie vegetable soup
directions: Bring water, tomato juice and tomatoes to a boil.
Add all other ingredients; cook until vegetables are tender.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger meat; drain and add taco seasoning. Mix in a large bowl the chopped lettuce, diced tomatoes, the drained kidney beans, black olives, shredded Cheddar cheese and tortilla chips. Then pour the whole bottle of Italian salad dressing.

title: frozen fruit
directions: Bring 3 cups water and sugar to a boil.
Let cool.
Add pineapple and oranges with juices.
Cut bananas into bite-size pieces and add to liquid mixture.
Drain maraschino cherries and cut in half.
Add to mixture.
Add orange juice and 1 can water. Freeze, stirring every hour.

title: charleston cheese dip
directions: Mix mayo, cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and onions.
Put mixture in greased quiche dish.
Top with crackers.
Remove from oven and top with bacon.
Serve with crackers.

title: praline pecans
directions: Melt butter.
Mix sugar and salt. Beat egg whites.
Fold in mixture and add pecans. Spread in pan and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.
Liquid will absorb.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Remove and place on wax paper to cool.

title: sara lee coffee cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding, water, oil, eggs, butter flavoring and vanilla.
Pour short half into greased sheet cake pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour rest of batter over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then drizzle glaze over the top.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling and pineapple in bottom of cake pan. Sprinkle entire cake mix on top.
Melt butter and drizzle over cake mix.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: aggie's fruit cobbler
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with the milk.
Put the oleo in an 8 x 13-inch pan and melt in oven.
Pour batter in pan.
Place the fruit on top. Do not stir.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: jillian's health bread
directions: Mix 4 cups wheat flour with salt.
Mix yeast with 1/2 cup warm water until dissolved.
Add all wet ingredients into flour and mix.
Add remaining ingredients; but add flour slowly; until dough is workable for kneading.
Knead for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: champayne salad
directions: Combine cream cheese (room temperature) and sugar.
Add fruits and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze for 30 minutes before serving.

title: jekyll island peanut pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk.
Blend and fold in whipped topping.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: butter crumb broccoli
directions: In 2-quart saucepan melt butter over medium heat; add parsley, onion, dill, salt and broccoli.
Cover; cook over medium heat until tender (5 to 6 minutes).
Remove cover; add pimiento and croutons, toss to coat and serve immediately.
Yields 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: country style ribs
directions: Place 4 pounds country style ribs in large pan; add enough water to cover.
Cover; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cook 1 hour. Remove ribs; drain.
Place bone side down on grill 3 inches from medium coals.
Cook about 30 minutes, turning frequently.

title: party biscuits
directions: Mix cream and flour.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick. Cut with
a
small
cutter, 1 1/4-inches diameter.
Place on a greased baking
sheet and bake at 400° for 8 minutes (time may vary). Open
and
place small pieces of cooked ham or a slice of link sausage inside.
Great for finger foods at parties.

title: orange walnuts
directions: Blend together fresh frozen orange juice (undiluted) with sugar and stir over low heat only until sugar is dissolved.
Heat to 240° without stirring, or until a small amount dropped in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and add walnuts.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken, then drop form a teaspoon onto sheets of waxed paper.
Allow to cool.

title: cherry pie jello
directions: Mix jello in boiling water until dissolved.
Add cold water. Place in refrigerator until it starts to set.
Then mix in the cherry pie filling.
Let set.
Place the Cool Whip on top.

title: hash brown au gratin(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Put potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch shallow baking dish. Add onions, cream and cheese and stir gently.
Pour butter evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut clusters candy(microwave)
directions: Place chocolate chips in large glass bowl and mix together. Place in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes on Medium power; stir halfway through.
Mix peanuts in and drop by the teaspoon onto wax paper; let harden.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix well and put in 12 muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Six muffins equals 1 protein, 1 bread, 1 vegetable, 1 milk and 2 fruit.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients; roll into small balls. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: honey mustard dipping sauce
directions: Stir all ingredients together in mixing bowl. Can be used as a dip or dressing.

title: great jello salad
directions: Set jello lightly.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firmly set.

title: homemade eagle brand
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/4 cups (10 ounces).

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Cook, but do not brown, sausage, celery, onions and pepper. Combine in a large kettle, water, soup mix, Worcestershire and rice.
Cook until rice is done (about 25 minutes), then add sausage mixture.
Put in casserole dish and bake in 350° oven about 1 1/2 hours.
Top with almonds if you like.
Serves 20.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Quarter
tomatoes,
put
through coarse grinder.
Drain off excess
liquid.
Measure
pulp to get 2 1/2 cups.
Combine tomatoes,
raisins,
butter
and
vinegar
in saucepan.
Blend together sugar,
cornstarch and spices.
Add to tomato mixture and stir
well.
Cook
over moderate heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Don't
get too dry, add little of the tomato juice if it
appears so.
Spoon mixture in unbaked pie shell, cover with top crust, slit.
Smooth small amount of cream over crust and sprinkle
with
little
sugar and cinnamon. Bake in preheated oven (425°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350°, continue baking 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole and bake about 1 hour at 325°.

title: crab meat fondue
directions: Heat on low burner until melted and smooth.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions and celery in olive oil.
Add tomatoes and paste; stir well.
Add garlic, sugar, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Stir and simmer 30 to 40 minutes; add shrimp.
Cook 15 minutes longer; add peas.
Serve over rice.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: About 25 minutes before serving:
In a 6-quart saucepot, prepare fettuccine as label directs; drain.
Return fettuccine to saucepot; over low heat, heat fettuccine, cream, Parmesan cheese, butter or margarine, salt and pepper.
Toss well.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 accompaniment servings; 330 calories per serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Trim flowerets from broccoli and blanch.
In heavy saucepan, melt butter and saute onions.
Stir in flour; whisk in broth and cream.
Stir until boiling.
Reduce heat.
Chop flowerets and add to soup.
Season to taste.
Heat through to meld flavors, but don't overcook.

title: spinach squares
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Add cheese and spinach.
Mix well. Spread into pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Add shortening, milk, vanilla and beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Add egg and beat another 2 minutes.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Cook in 350° oven until lightly brown, about 30 minutes.
Spread layers and sides and top of warm cake with cooked frosting.
Cover with coconut.

title: old fashioned carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in carrots and nuts.
Pour into three 8 or 9-inch prepared cake pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze dry the spinach.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve with pumpernickel bread.

title: frozen salad
directions: Stir
together the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Blend together
the
creamed
cheese and salad dressing, then stir into the mixture in the bowl.
Fold in the whipped cream.

title: sicilian meat loaf
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients on waxed paper or foil; pat the meat mixture to form a 10 x 12-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham and cheese on top of meat mixture, leaving 1/2-inch margin all around. Roll up jellyroll style.
Place meat, seam side down, in pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours; add cheese slices if desired on the top.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: condensed milk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn oven to 300° and bake another hour.
Test with a knife, if not done bake 30 minutes longer.

title: country style meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, mixed vegetables (thawed), salt, pepper and parsley in a deep mixing bowl; mix well.
Add salt, pepper, corn flakes and 1/2 of tomato soup (undiluted).
Mix well to blend. Place 1/2 of the meat mixture in a buttered 6 x 16 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish; pack.
Dot top with 1/2 of the butter.
Place rest of meat mixture in baking dish.
Dot with rest of butter and pour rest of soup over the top.
In a preheated 375° oven, bake 1 hour. Remove.
Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in 2 or 3 small casseroles.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: cherry slices
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually. Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Gradually add to shortening mixture, beating well.
Spread in a greased 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan.
Reserve a little more than a cup of batter.
Spread cherry pie filling to within 1/2-inch from edges of pan.
Place remaining dough by spoonfuls on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: gazpacho
directions: Liquefy in blender.
When ready to serve, dilute with cold water and/or chicken broth to desired consistency.

title: no fall-apart tacos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet, brown ground beef until crumbly.
Drain fat.
Add taco seasonings and water per package directions.
Cook as directed.
Fill each taco shell with 3 tablespoons meat; place on baking sheet.
Bake in oven 5 minutes.
Do not use toast, broil or top brown settings.
Top each taco with lettuce, cheese and tomatoes.
Garnish with chunky salsa, sliced ripe olives, chopped onion if desired.

title: stuffed sole
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 35 minutes, divided.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugars well.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually blend in flour, salt and baking soda which have been sifted together.

title: german pork chops
directions: Saute onion and apple in margarine and pour in sauerkraut. Place pork chops over kraut.
Cover and cook until chops are tender.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 1 dozen.
Makes 6 servings.

title: can't pass 'em byes
directions: Melt almond bark and peanut butter together in microwave. Combine the next 4 ingredients and pour peanut butter mixture over.
Mix well.
Put on paper towels or waxed paper with a teaspoon.
Work fast as it hardens fast.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine in top of a double boiler sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over hot water until thick, stirring constantly. Add egg yolks and cook another 3 minutes.
Add butter; cool.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour into a baked pie shell and let cool.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix berries and Sure-Jell.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Mix Karo good and add sugar, 1 cup at a time, stirring after each.
Put into containers and freeze.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together until smooth. Add the beaten eggs, oil and sugar along with the zucchini.

title: homemade manicotti shells
directions: In medium bowl, combine eggs, flour, salt and water.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Let stand 1/2 hour, no longer.
Slowly heat 8 inch skillet.
Pour 1/4 c. batter, rotating skillet quickly to spread batter evenly.
Cook over med. heat until top is dry. Completely use batter, putting wax paper between each.
Freeze until you fill.
Use your own ricotta filling with your own sauce.

title: christmas mix
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a large pan. I use a disposable turkey roaster pan. Melt white chocolate in microwave on medium high for 2-3 minutes. Stir after 1 minute. If chocolate has softened after 2 minutes, add 3 tablespoons oil. Stir. Then microwave 10-20 seconds until smooth. Pour chocolate mixture over mix, cover well. Pour onto kitchen counter. Spread well, not too thick. Mixture will probably harden in 20-30 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and butter; add eggs 1 at a time.
Add vanilla, lemon, milk and flour.
Bake in round cake pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes (start in cold oven).

title: nacho chicken
directions: Melt butter; add celery, onions and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Mix soups and milk; cook until soup is dissolved.
Add vegetable mixture to soup base.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, put a layer of chips and layer of chicken.
Pour about half of soup base over these layers.
Lay sliced cheese on this.
Add another layer of chips, chicken, then remaining soup base.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: turkey balls
directions: Mix well; form balls and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Mix melted margarine, vanilla and milk. Add to sugar and cocoa mix.
Stir constantly on medium heat. Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add oats.
Drop out by spoon onto a piece of plastic wrap.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar and vinegar.
Drain beets and add juice to cornstarch mixture.
Cook until thick and clear.
Add oleo and stir until melted.
Add drained beets and heat through. This amount will glaze 3 to 4 cans of beets.

title: french fried zucchini
directions: Heat 1 inch of oil in 10-inch skillet to 375°.
Mix baking mix and salt.
Dip zucchini into egg; coat with baking mixture.
Fry about 1/3 of the zucchini at a time, turning if necessary until golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: blueberry kuchen
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar. Cut in 1/2 cup butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Press into bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with blueberries.
Combine 1 cup sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle mixture over fruit.
Dot with butter, if desired. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Combine sour cream and egg yolks.
Spread over fruit.
Set oven to 350° and return to oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peppermint meringue drops
directions: When you're out of an ingredient, improvise.
It's more convenient than making a frantic trip to the store.
Check your shelves to see if you can substitute other ingredients already on hand.
To remember how, clip this handy chart and post it in a kitchen cupboard.

title: millionaire's candy
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler.
Stir in nuts, spoon on waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate and wax together.
Dip caramel in the chocolate.
Let cool.

title: uncooked oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together quick oats, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts. Bring to a boil the milk, butter, sugar and salt.
Add milk mixture to oats until all blended.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Cool.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook green onion, ham and garlic in butter in stock pot over medium-low heat until onions are tender.
Add broth, Knorr leek soup mix, cabbage, potatoes and bay leaf; simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in cream and continue to simmer until heated through.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish individual servings with parsley or chives.
Serves 8.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put all ingredients in large plastic bag and shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Pour potatoes into shallow pan and bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped, fresh parsley.
Serves 8.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Drain.
Leave 2 tablespoons of bacon fat in pan.
Add onions and cook until soft not brown. Combine beans, applesauce, molasses, Worcestershire, vinegar and mustard.
Put in 3-quart casserole dish.
Stir in onion and reserved crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Note: You can substitute your favorite vegetable combination.

title: coconut lush
directions: Mix the butter, chopped nuts and flour together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: fruit cocktail orange jello salad
directions: Heat fruit cocktail until hot.
Add Jell-O.
Stir well and let cool until it thickens.
Whip cream cheese and add Cool Whip. Stir until well blended.
Add to the fruit and Jell-O, mixing well.
Pour into Pyrex pan and sprinkle nuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Put pudding mix and milk in bowl and beat.
Stir in Cool Whip and miniature marshmallows.
Add pecans and pineapple.
Stir.

title: jelly roll
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat whole eggs until foamy.
Add sugar to eggs and mix.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add dry ingredients to other mixture; mix well.
Put in vanilla and beat.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet or shallow pan.
Bake until brown.
Immediately after removing from oven, pour jelly on.
Spread out well.
Roll up and let cool.
Unwrap it and wrap in wax paper.
(I put in old cloth to cool.)

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Add 2 cups strawberries; mash strawberries in saucepan with potato masher. Bring to simmer, stirring until thickened.
Cool to lukewarm.
Cut cake lengthwise to make 3 layers.
Spread about 2 1/2 tablespoons of strawberry mixture between each layer.
Sandwich layers together.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; mash in small bowl.
Stir in dressing, relish, mustard and seasonings until smooth.
Spoon or pipe into centers of egg whites.
Cover; refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 16.

title: guatemalan soup
directions: Soak rice in enough water to cover. After rice has absorbed water and softened, drain. Combine all ingredients and grind well. Add meat stock and mix well. Simmer all ingredients until cooked. Serve hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish. Top with cheese and stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dieters delight
directions: Put angel food cake mix in bowl.
Stir in crushed pineapple (juice and all).
The juice from the pineapple will serve in place of the liquid to mix your cake.
Be sure to stir in...do not use a mixer.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake as directed on cake box.
Remove from oven.
Take a toothpick and poke holes in cake.
Mix your Jello in a bowl; pour over cake.
Refrigerate and let Jello set up.
Spread Cool Whip (can be fat-free) over Jello. Cut and serve.

title: hearty hamburger supper
directions: Boil potatoes (don't cream). Brown meat and drain off fat. Stir in soup; do not add water.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve mixture spooned over boiled potatoes that have been mashed with a fork.

title: shrimp and asparagus stir fry
directions: Heat the butter and olive oil in large skillet.
Add asparagus, bell pepper, and mushrooms.
Saute until tender crisp. Add salt, if needed.
Add shrimp and stir fry until shrimp turns pink.
Sprinkle with sauce mix and soy sauce.
Mix well. Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Stir together peanut butter and margarine.
Gradually add sugar, stirring until combined (can do this with hands).
Shape into balls and put on waxed paper.
Let stand until dry (about 20 minutes).
Melt chocolate.
Cool slightly.
Dip balls into melted chocolate, letting excess drip off.
Place on waxed paper.
Let stand until coating is dry.
Makes about 30 pieces; can be doubled.

title: butterscotch nut bars
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Remove from heat; blend in sugar. Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add vanilla.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add all at once.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Gently stir in chopped nuts.
Turn into greased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Spread dough evenly with spatula. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Cool cookies in pan.
If desired, drizzle with glaze.

title: easter bunny cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 2 round pans (9 or 8 x 1 1/2 inches) as directed on package.
Freeze one layer for later use.
Cut the other cake layer into halves to make 2 semicircles.
Prepare frosting mix as directed on package.
Put halves of cake together with frosting to form body.
Place cake upright on cut edge on serving plate or tray.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Take out and cool.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
While this is cooking, in a skillet with butter, cook onions, bell peppers and celery until tender.
Add tomato soup, mushroom soup, chili powder, Ro-Tel and mushrooms.
Mix well and add spaghetti and chicken.
Put into casserole and top with cheese slices.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together and knead as for bread for 5 minutes.
Knead each day for 3 days.
On the 4th day, shape into long logs, approximately 3 rolls each recipe.
Place on a jelly roll (or shallow) pan.
Bake 8 hours at 125°.
Turn once after 4 hours.
Cool and refrigerate.
Best if placed on a wire rack in pan when baked.

title: vodka slush
directions: Boil 2 cups water with sugar until dissolved.
Boil additional 2 cups of water with tea bags.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Remove tea bags.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Fold in chips and 1/2 of chocolate bar.
Bake in a greased, unfloured tube pan for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle rest of grated chocolate on top while cake is hot.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, garlic and onion.
Add tomato, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Spray 9 x 13 inch pan with Pam (cooking spray). Line bottom with 6 tortillas.

title: swedish nuts
directions: In bowl, beat egg whites.
Pour over walnuts.
Add brown sugar and mix.
Melt oleo on cookie sheets.
Spread coated nuts onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, then turn nuts. Continue to bake about 45 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: hot crawfish dip
directions: Mix margarine and cream cheese in large mixing bowl until smooth.
Add seasonings and beat until fluffy.
Stir in minced crawfish.
Spoon into ovenproof glass dish and heat at 350° until just hot throughout.
Serve with sourdough bread or Melba toast. Serves 20.

title: strawberry banana shake
directions: Slice the bananas.
Combine the bananas, strawberries, milk and 1 pint of the ice cream in a blender in batches.
Blend until the mixture is smooth.
Pour the milk shake into 4 tall glasses and top each with a scoop of the remaining ice cream.
Garnish with a fresh strawberry.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Roll up chicken breasts.
Wrap 2 slices of smoked beef around each breast.
Hold together with a toothpick.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken, which has been placed in a baking dish.
Cover and bake 3 hours at 350°.

title: kathleen's famous pork hawaiian kabobs(serves 4 adults)
directions: You will also need 1 package of wooden skewers.
On wooden skewer, alternate pieces of pork, pepper, onion, pineapple and cherry while alternating one piece of bacon woven between pieces.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugars, oil and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients; mix well. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and lightly floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Test for doneness with a toothpick. Stores well in freezer for several months.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed only using 1 cup of water.
Add orange jello.
Bake according to directions on box.
When cool, split the layers.
Mix sour cream, sugar, coconut and orange juice.
Put in fridge before you make the cake.
When cake is cool, frost layers upside down until the last layer.
Reserve 1 cup of filling to mix with 8 ounce carton of Cool Whip for icing top and sides. Refrigerate overnight (very good).

title: st. patrick's day salad
directions: Prepare gelatin as directed on box.
Arrange pitted cherries in mold and pour 1/2 of gelatin on top.
Chill until firm and add remaining gelatin.
Serve on lettuce leaves with dressing and cottage cheese.

title: cranberry-orange cup
directions: In
a
2 quart saucepan, stir together all ingredients, except orange
juice.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Strain.
Stir
in
orange juice; heat, but do not boil. Serve hot.	Garnish with cinnamon sticks, if desired.

title: cold cream cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Top with fresh strawberries, blueberries or any other fruit desired.

title: rice krispy bars
directions: Place 1/4 c. butter in a 12 x 7 glass dish.
Microwave on medium for 1 minute or until butter is melted.
Stir in 40 large marshmallows.
Microwave for 1 minute on medium or until they are softened.
Stir until smooth.
Mix in 5 cups of Rice Krispies. Press down with spatula and allow to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: tangy-tart drink
directions: Combine chilled juices.
Add 7-Up or ginger ale.
Add ice cubes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix well.
Place in an 8 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
You may also add 1 cup of chopped nuts to the top before cooking.

title: uncle james' barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add vinegar and all other ingredients.
Bring to a slow boil; simmer for a few minutes.
Great on chicken.
We like it best on grilled pork.

title: pepper-chicken fettucini toss(36.1 mg cholesterol)
directions: Prepare fettuccini as package directs and drain . In large skillet, heat oil; add chicken, peppers, onion, mushrooms and seasoning.
Cook and stir over medium heat until chicken is cooked through 8 to 10 minutes.
Add hot cooked fettuccini.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, baking soda and salt together in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil in a medium mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes until well blended.
Add eggs; beat until light and lemon-colored.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine and line bottom only of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs, sugar and margarine in large bowl and beat at medium speed for 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over graham crackers.
Drain pineapple and spread evenly over mixture in pan.
Slice bananas and put on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Cover whole mixture with nuts and cherries. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Let set overnight.
Take out 1 hour ahead.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned on top.
Serves about 8.

title: cheese-olive balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small bowl, combine cheese with margarine.
Blend thoroughly with large wooden spoon.
In separate dish, combine salt, paprika and flour.
Blend flour mixture into cheese mixture.
Measure one teaspoon of mixture and shape around olive, keeping the pimento uncovered.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes.
Dough will spread out while baking.

title: chocolate kiss
directions: Melt and stir until blended.
Grease the inside of a Tupperware funnel, blocking the end with foil.
Pour in chocolate mixture; chill and let set.
Unmold when completely hardened, then wrap in foil.
It's a perfect present or treat for the kids.

title: bread and butter pickles(must prepare ahead.  makes 5 pints)
directions: Place cucumbers and onions in large colander.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand for 1 hour.
Rinse well with cold water and drain thoroughly.
In large pot, place cucumber and onions; add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook about 5 minutes. Ladle into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: bran muffins
directions: Prepare muffin tins for 18 muffins.
Sift white flour, baking powder and soda.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Beat egg, sour milk, oil together in separate bowl.
Combine with dry ingredients with a few swift strokes.
Fold in raisins; fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes in 425° oven.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Heat milk and butter in microwave to lukewarm.
Stir in sugar. Sprinkle yeast on top.
Stir in enough flour to make a batter (should resemble cake mix batter).
Cover with warm towel and let rise 45 minutes.
Add more flour, baking soda, powder and salt. Mix well to make moist dough consistency.
Refrigerate.
When ready to cook, roll dough, cut into circles and let rise on pan again 2 hours before baking at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peas and carrots tarragon
directions: Scrape carrots.
Remove ends and cut into matchstick pieces. Drop into boiling salted water.
Cook 4 minutes.
Drain, then plunge into ice water.
Remove immediately; drain well and set aside or refrigerate.
At serving time, place peas in a sieve or colander.
Run hot water over peas; drain well.
Melt butter or margarine in large skillet.
Add onion.
Cook until onion is partially tender.
Add peas and carrots.
Shake skillet and gently stir vegetables over medium heat until heated through, about 5 minutes.
Toss with parsley and tarragon.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat margarine, sugars, egg and water until creamy.
Combine and add flour, salt and baking soda to creamy mixture.
Add raisins and rolled oats.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: sue's raspberry pull apart bread
directions: Slice each loaf into 8 slices.
Cut each slice in fourths, making 64 pieces.
Spread these in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan. Mix Jell-O, sugars and spices.
Add nuts and sprinkle evenly over bread. Dab butter over all.
Let rise to top of pan.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Take from oven and turn upside down on a cookie sheet so juices run through the pull apart rolls. Delicious.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet, then drain.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Add all ingredients.
Pour in a covered dish and bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: green beef enchiladas
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, milk and Velveeta cheese and heat over medium heat until cheese melts.
Add green chilies and set aside.
Brown meat with onion and drain.

Add chili powder, cumin (and salt and pepper if desired) to meat mixture and mix well. Warm tortillas in microwave or in warm skillet, one at a time. Put meat mixture and grated Cheddar cheese in tortilla and roll up.
Arrange tortilla rolls in long baking dish and pour soup mixture over all.
Top with additional Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: dressing for fresh vegetables or slaw
directions: Mix together and use with fresh broccoli and cauliflower or slaw or as a dip.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and place in a loaf pan or form into a loaf.
Bake at 350° approximately 2 hours.

title: sweet barbecue
directions: Cook roast with garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce to taste in cooking bag or pressure cooker.
Remove when done.
Tear roast into small pieces.
Place in skillet; add barbecue sauce and honey.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer on medium for 15 to 20 minutes.
Adjust amount of honey to suit taste.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in shallow 4 quart dish.
Pour in milk; sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread crumbs are browned and cabbage tender.

title: pound cake(do not preheat oven)
directions: Cream well margarine, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, 2 at a time and milk, 1 egg last. Add all flavorings. Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 300°.

title: yeast rolls(feather light)
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl except 1 cup flour (use this one cup to roll out rolls) and yeast.
Beat smooth; add yeast mixture.
Let rise in warm place for 1 hour or until double in size.
Pour dough out over the 1 cup flour; knead until smooth, roll out to 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Place into greased pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Brush with butter.
Shape into loaf, if desired and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Recipe makes one loaf.

title: koyane-yaki
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in oil until limp.
Cut 4 (12-inch) squares of aluminum foil and oil tops.
Scatter sauteed onions and mushrooms in the middle of each foil square.
Place salmon fillets on top, skin side down.
Whip egg yolks and 1 cup vegetable oil to foamy stage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon sauce over fillets. Fold and seal packets securely and place in baking dish.
Bake in 550° oven for 10 to 15 minutes depending on thickness of fillets. Place packets on plate with fresh lemon.

title: seafood dip
directions: Melt all ingredients together and serve with Escort crackers.

title: orange sherbet jello salad
directions: Pour both packages of gelatin in boiling water, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Gradually add orange sherbet, stirring to melt.
Stir in pineapple and oranges.
Pour into an 8-inch square dish or a 10 x 6-inch dish; refrigerate to congeal.
Serve topped with nondairy whipped topping, if desired.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend the cream cheese, powdered sugar, margarine and vanilla. Add coconut and nuts. Frost. Chill in refrigerator for best taste. Serves 16. Can freeze. Must do ahead. Tastes best if cold.

title: best waffles ever
directions: Heat waffle iron.
Beat eggs.
Beat in remaining ingredients with a rotary beater until smooth.
Pour batter into center of waffle iron and bake.

title: curried potatoes
directions: Wash and cut potatoes into wedges (leave skins on).
Melt butter.
Add curry powder.
Toss wedges in butter and curry powder mixture.
Bake in single layer on baking sheet at 350° until browned.
Toss baked potatoes with salt in a brown paper bag and serve.

title: salsa di vongoli(spaghetti and clams)
directions: Heat oil in pan and brown garlic.
Add parsley, oregano and clams.
Cook only for 2 to 3 minutes.
Prolonged cooking toughens clams.
Makes enough sauce for 1 pound spaghetti or other macaroni.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Add sifted meal, flour, soda, baking powder and salt; mix together and add onion. Shape by dropping from tablespoon into hot oil after cooking your fish.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: angel's delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and refrigerate.
Mix powdered milk and water and refrigerate.
When jello starts to gel add powdered milk.
Pour over graham cracker crust and sprinkle with nuts if desired.

title: sweet spiced nuts
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine sugar, water, salt, cinnamon, allspice, cloves and nutmeg.
Cook at high 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until sugar is melted; stir in nuts.
Cook at high 4 to 5 minutes or until syrup begins to harden.
Immediately pour nut mixture onto buttered cookie sheet.
Spread thinly.
Cool; break into small pieces.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: sinful potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine frozen potatoes, sour cream and cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake until bubbly at 325° (about 30 minutes).

title: cream cheese cookies(no eggs)
directions: With mixer, blend cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Add flour and blend.
Mix in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet or sheet covered with parchment baking paper.
Bake in oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook hamburger; warm beans.
Put ground beef, refried beans and cheese in a cake pan.
Heat it until cheese is melted, with olives and onions on it.
Then put tomatoes, sour cream, guacamole and the rest of cheese on.
Then it's ready to eat with some chips.

title: mom's chili
directions: Brown together hamburg and onion; drain grease.
In a crock-pot or pot, add hamburg mixture, garlic to taste, baked beans, tomato sauce, salt to taste, chili powder and taco sauce. Simmer for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: fruity ham
directions: Grate zest from orange slice flesh and put into casserole with zest, apples, onion, celery, apricots, spice and 2 tablespoons of the vinegar.
Mix mustard with honey and remaining vinegar. Spread over ham and place in casserole.
Cover tightly, cooking about 2 hours (or as specified on ham package) at 325°.
Remove ham.
Keep warm.
Press contents of casserole through sieve and reheat sauce gently in saucepan.
Pour sauce into sauce boat. Serve with ham.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil; remove.
Brown garlic and onion.
Add sauce and spices.
Layer chops in the sauce; let come to a boil. Add mushrooms and green peppers until cooked.

title: mexican relish dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate overnight and serve with taco flavored chips or white corn tortilla chips (my favorite). Serves 10 to 12.

title: crybaby molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugars; add butter and cream until smooth.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add molasses.
Combine dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Add slowly to creamed mixture.
Form dough in small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 5 dozen.

title: no fail crust
directions: Combine dry ingredients together.
Cut in the Crisco.
Add enough water (ice cold) to egg yolks to make 1 cup.
Pour over flour.
Makes 6 crusts.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and seal in large jar.
Add several teaspoons of mix to a cup of boiling water (to taste).

title: ann's blueberry torte
directions: Mix cream cheese, warmed, with powdered sugar.
Spread on crust.
Whip cream with sugar.
Spread on cheese.
Put on one layer of miniature marshmallows; one layer well drained crushed pineapple; layer of blueberry pie filling.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and chill.

title: blueberry pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Mix pumpkin and milk until blended.
Cream shortening and sugar in mixer bowl.
Add egg; beat until mixture if fluffy.
Add flour mixture alternately with pumpkin mixture, beating well.
Combine blueberries and 1 tablespoon flour.
Gently stir into batter.
Fill 18 paper lined muffin tins 3/4 full.
Sprinkle streusel over top of muffins. Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes or until done.

title: walking tacos
directions: Brown hamburger.
Spread beans in serving dish.
Layer hamburger over beans.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer guacamole, ground onions, grated cheese, sour cream and sprinkle with chopped olives.
Serve with salsa if desired.

title: apple sheet cake
directions: Sift
flour, baking powder and instant pudding mix.
Mix sugar,
eggs
and oil.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately, mixing well.
Stir	in
apples
and
dash of salt.	Bake in 9 x 13-inch, greased and floured pan for 40 minutes in a 350° oven. Ice with your favorite cream cheese icing after cake cools.

title: cheesecake cups
directions: You will also need 24 foil muffin cups.

title: shake and bake
directions: Combine ingredients and use to coat chicken or pork chops.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Lightly brown the meat in butter, keeping it crumbly.
Cut tops from onion; add to meat.
Cut potatoes and carrots and place over ground beef in skillet.
Season.
Cover and simmer over low heat until vegetables are tender (might be necessary to add a little water).
Add green beans and soup and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: raw pear cake
directions: Drain juice from ground pears.
Add soda to pears and let stand.
Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add egg and mix well.
Add pear mixture, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Bake in a 9 x 10-inch greased pan, about 40 minutes, in a 350° oven.

title: baklazhan
directions: Bake eggplant at 450° until soft to the touch.
Remove skin, chop pulp almost to a puree.
Fry onions in oil until soft; stir in chopped green peppers and fry 6 minutes longer.
Skin tomatoes and chop coarsely; add to onions.
Add eggplant and all seasoning. Cook, uncovered, until mixture is thick enough to spread . Chill until ready to serve on black pumpernickel or sesame crackers.

title: basil-garlic squash
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Brush squash and zucchini with one-half of mixture.
Spray grill rack with vegetable spray oil. Place vegetables (cut side down) over medium-hot coals.
Cook 3 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining mixture.
Continue to cook an additional 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 8.

title: grandmother's white sugar cookies
directions: Roll quite thin; cut in cookie shapes.
Bake on cookie sheet to light brown.
Place in a 400° oven for 8 minutes.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Mix ingredients in large pot and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: honey cream cheese pears
directions: Drain pears and reserve syrup.
Mix cream cheese with honey until well blended.
Arrange pears in a baking dish and fill hollows with cream cheese mixture, dividing evenly.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs and pour reserved syrup around pears.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes or until well heated.

title: lib's fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter.
Pour into powdered sugar and cocoa and mix well.
Add 1 Tbsp. vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into two 13 X 9 inch buttered pans.
Pat down and refrigerate.
Freezes well.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar, milk and melted butter in bowl; mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Spoon undrained peaches over batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
May substitute nutmeg for cinnamon.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
Add sugar and eggs; sift dry ingredients together into a bowl.
Add vanilla to creamed mixture.
Alternate dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture until completely mixed.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 325° for about 80 to 90 minutes.

title: spider cookies
directions: Combine butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in a 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes (after 1 minute, stir).
Add noodles.
Stir to coat noodles.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on waxed paper.
Top with two raisins or cherries.
Let harden on waxed paper.

title: white pear cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour in prepared Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine the brown sugar, oleo, corn syrup and salt; heat to boiling.
Boil for 5 minutes in a large kettle.
After removing from heat, mix in the soda and vanilla; pour this mixture over popped corn.
Place in shallow pan; bake for 1 hour at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and break.

title: sweet sour 3 bean salad
directions: Drain all beans and rinse with cold water.
Put in a large bowl.
Add the celery and onion.
Marinate overnight in the following dressing.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix flour with sugar and stir into eggs.
Add butter, then buttermilk and flavorings.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake for about 40 minutes.

title: something good - chow chow
directions: Grind all vegetables.
Mix together; add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir well.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Can in sterilized jars.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add sifted flour, soda, salt and spices.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in sliced apples and nuts or use nuts to sprinkle over top.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan for about 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Serve warm with powdered sugar dusted over top or whipped cream. Even nice with vanilla ice cream.
I sometimes use as a breakfast dish as well.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and slice bananas in juice.
Drain liquid from fruit cocktail and mix instant pudding into liquid.
Mix pineapple, fruit cocktail and juice together.

title: roger's kentucky pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; add margarine and vanilla.
Stir in eggs.
Mix all together.
Stir in pecans, then chocolate morsels.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower, carrot and onion until extra tender.
Then run through blender.
Add half and half, margarine, milk, bacon and the Velveeta cheese to taste.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Can put in cream of mushroom soup or thicken milk with flour.

title: grandma's string beans
directions: Finely chop bacon and fry in saucepan.
Add green beans with bacon and grease.
Cook on low, stirring often.
Add a dash of garlic salt.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water or pineapple juice for 5 minutes. Dissolve in boiling water.
Add salt, sugar, vinegar and lemon juice, mix and cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, add the remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Drain broccoli except 2 tablespoons liquid.
Add Velveeta cheese and 1/4 stick butter.
Stir until melted, then place in casserole.
Mix 1/2 roll Ritz crackers with 1/2 stick butter. Spread crumbs over casserole.
Bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: green beans
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion.
Cook until wilted.
Add Worcestershire sauce and sugar, then add other ingredients and simmer until tender.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed; rinse in cold water.

title: taco chicken rice
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, add rice, turn off heat, let sit 5 minutes, serve over chips or shells, top with cheese.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix well; batter will be thick.
Dip with 1-inch dipper.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: tomato-raspberry jello salad
directions: Add water to chopped tomatoes to make 4 cups.
Bring to a boil.
Add a large package jello.
Add celery, green pepper and dash of hot sauce.
Refrigerate to set.
Delicious.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix and pour into an 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: country chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in large pot; add water, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; cover and cook until tender (about 45 minutes to 1 hour). Remove chicken from broth; take chicken off bones and cut into bite size pieces.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Combine oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, soda and baking powder. Stir in nuts and coconut.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet and press flat with fork.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions on package.
Add the pineapple juice and the orange juice.
Chill.
Add the ginger ale just before serving.

title: browned rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice and cook over medium heat until rice is light brown.
Stir as it browns.
Pour rice and butter into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Add soups and mushrooms and stir.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Taste before serving and add salt, if needed.
The soup and consomme will partly season rice.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: rhubarb dream dessert
directions: Press into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Beat on medium speed until smooth, spread on pie shell and sprinkle with pecans.
In another bowl, beat remaining 3 eggs.
Add syrup, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and 1 tsp. vanilla, beat until blended.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 375 degrees about 40 minutes.

title: yams made easy
directions: In a medium size pan, mix half of the syrup from the canned yams, butter, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla extract and pancake syrup.
Bring to boil.
Add yams and marshmallows.
Let cook on low-medium fire for about 10 minutes.

title: larry's louisiana dirty rice
directions: Boil chicken livers in large saucepan in 2 quarts water. Season with approximately 1 1/2 tablespoons salt and 1/2 teaspoon each black and red pepper.
Cook covered for 45 minutes over medium fire.
Add more water as needed.
Remove livers from broth and set both aside.

title: flank steak
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate steak in the refrigerator for at least 4 hours or more. Grill. It's excellent!

title: tomato sauce
directions: In bacon drippings or cooking oil, brown chopped onion, green pepper,
banana
pepper,
mushrooms and onion tops.
Add sugar. When browned,
add
tomatoes
and
cook slowly for 1/2 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion; drain and put in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Mix cream of celery soup with milk; pour over meat mixture. Top with Tater Tots (or hash browns), enough to cover ground beef mixture. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes. Uncover and bake another 10 to 15 minutes to brown potatoes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: country chicken
directions: Line bottom of cookie sheet with beef.
Place chicken on top and cover with the soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with flavored rice, such as curry or saffron instead of vegetable and potato or salad.

title: vermont pork chops
directions: Lightly brown pork chops in the oil.
Place chops in flat baking dish.
Combine other ingredients over low heat and pour over chops.
Cover and bake 45 minutes in a 400° oven, basting occasionally.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Place chops on warming platter.
Make a sauce by combining pan juices with the flour over low heat.
Stir until slightly thickened, about 2 minutes.
Serve sauce over chops.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Combine raisins
and water, boil 5 minutes.
(Should be 1/2 cup liquid	left,
if
not,
add
water.) Drain water off. When cool, add
soda
to
it.
Blend
shortening with salt and spice. Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Add eggs, vanilla and cooled raisin
soda mixture.
Add flour sifted with baking powder.
Stir in	raisins
and
nuts.
Chill.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by rounded teaspoonful.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon-poppyseed coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease square (9 x 9 x 2-inch) pan. Mix all ingredients, except glaze, beat 30 seconds.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown and wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze.
Makes 9 servings.

title: broiled shrimp kabobs
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, leaving tails intact.
Put shrimp in a heavy-duty plastic bag.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over shrimp.
Seal bag securely and shake well.
Marinate shrimp in refrigerator for at least 40 minutes.
Turn bag occasionally. Remove shrimp from marinade and thread evenly onto 12-inch skewers.
Place kabobs on rack of broiler pan coated with cooking spray.
Broil 5 1/2 inches from heat with electric oven door partially opened, 3 to 4 minutes on each side, or until done. Yield: 4 servings.

title: cold pizza
directions: Bake crescent rolls according to directions on package for pizza crust.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese, salad dressing, dill weed and taco seasoning.
Spread on crust.
Top with raw vegetables and olives.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.

title: lemon spice bars
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs, lemon peel and juice; beat well. Sift together flour, baking powder and spices; add to creamed mixture. Stir in rolled oats and nuts. Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pack at least 3/4 of the mixture firmly in the bottom of the pan.
Cream together cream cheese and Cool Whip until smooth.
(Add a few drops of mix if hard to blend.)
Spread on crust.
Top with pie filling and sprinkle remaining graham cracker crumbs over all.
Chill several hours.

title: toffee bar cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine sugar and flour on low speed in a mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mix resembles small peas. Reserve 1/2 cup mixture for topping.
Add milk, egg, vanilla, baking soda and salt to remaining crumb mix.
Transfer to pan.
Add Heath bar bits to reserved crumbs, along with nuts.
Sprinkle on cake.
Bake about 35 minutes until done.

title: pork casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add celery, peppers and onion.
Brown lightly. Add water and simmer until tender.
Add soup and rice.
Mix. Put into casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: cranberry cottage pudding
directions: Beat egg, add sugar and oil.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add with milk to egg mixture.
Add cranberries.
Put into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with warm lemon sauce.

title: marshmallow waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice on apples.
Add everything else and enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Toss lightly.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch pie plate.
Whisk together eggs and sugar in large bowl; add butter and next 4 ingredients, stirring until blended.
Stir in pecans and spoon into prepared pie plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
(Mixture will rise, then fall as it cools.)
Serve with ice cream and chocolate sauce, if desired.

title: six weeks bran muffin mix
directions: Put 2 cups bran in the boiling water and let stand.
In large separate bowl, mix melted shortening, remaining bran, sugar, slightly beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Add bran, softened in water. Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Combine flour with other ingredients and stir to blend.
Store mix in refrigerator until ready to bake.
When ready to cook, fill well-greased muffin tins approximately half full.
Bake at 400° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields about 60 muffins.
Mixture will keep approximately six weeks.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order as listed.
Refrigerate and let set overnight. Toss before serving.

title: bearnaise sauce
directions: Combine wine, shallots and tarragon and cook until wine is reduced to a mere glaze.
Combine glaze with egg yolks and salt in blender.
Heat butter until bubbling hot.
Turn blender on and off once quickly to blend ingredients.
Turn on again and gradually pour melted butter in steady stream until sauce thickens. Additional tarragon or parsley may be folded into sauce. Excellent on broiled beef, fish or eggs.

title: caribbean pineapple ginger cooler
directions: In large saucepan, bring water to boil; add pineapple and gingerroot and let mixture cool to room temperature, tightly covered.
(The mixture may be left to steep overnight).

title: easy banana bread
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add bananas. Sift flour, salt and soda; add to mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Stir in candy and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Drop by half teaspoonful onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: icing
directions: Mix and boil 2 minutes.
Pour over cake while warm.

title: mushroom macaroni
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and mushrooms in 1 tablespoon oil and 3 tablespoons butter for about 15 minutes.
Add another 3 tablespoons butter and stir until melted.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper and the cayenne.
Bring to boil and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in macaroni and 2 tablespoons parsley.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons of butter. Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, 1 tablespoon parsley, 1 tablespoon oil and the melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake until browned, about 25 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch skillet.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
10 to 12 small servings.

title: old fashion beef barley soup
directions: Brown meat with onions.
In large pan, put in browned meat with onions, water, potatoes, celery, carrots, tomatoes, barley and spices.
Simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Add corn, peas and string beans; simmer 10 more minutes.
Add all liquids from the cans of vegetables.

title: chicken cacciatora
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add chicken and brown slowly.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Cook onions and garlic until tender. Combine remaining ingredients, except wine.
Return chicken to skillet and simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir in wine.
Cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into a buttered baking dish.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for one hour, stirring occasionally.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add boiling water. Stir and cool. Add sugar, lemon juice and undrained pineapple.
Chill.
Mix 2/3 of the Cool Whip with the gelatin mixture.
Break cake into small pieces (1-inch cubes).
Alternate layers of cake pieces and gelatin mixture in a 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Chill at least 6 hours or overnight.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut over top.
Chill 3 or more hours.
Serves 16 to 20 people.

title: mom's burnt sugar cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add water, flour and egg yolks and beat together 5 minutes, then add burnt sugar and vanilla.
Sift together flour and baking powder and beat into mixture.
Add 2 beaten egg whites and fold into cake batter.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and fruit pulp; mix well. Sift flour with salt, soda and spices.
Add to mixture.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour with yeast in large mixing bowl.
Heat milk, sugar, shortening until shortening is almost totally melted. Add to flour mixture.
Add egg. Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute. Then beat on high for 3 minutes.
Mix remainder of flour by hand to make soft dough.
Shape into ball.

title: mamaw's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour with a wire whisk.
Beat eggs thoroughly. Add eggs, corn syrup and oleo to sugar/flour mixture; mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock pizza
directions: Cook and drain noodles according to the directions. Brown ground beef and onions. Drain fat. Add the sauces and optional ingredients to the meat and simmer. Layer in 9 x 13 pan twice the noodles, meat sauce, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange butter bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar in the usual way.
Add egg, vanilla and grated orange rind mixing until blended well. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add orange juice to milk.
Alternate the flour and the milk mixture into the creamed butter and sugar. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 40 minutes until done. Remove from pan and cool. Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Add an ice ring, if desired. Yields 6 1/2 quarts.

title: brownie mix
directions: Mix with a dry whisk and store in an airtight container.

title: chicken salad
directions: Dice chicken very fine.
Add all ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Also, olives are very good in this recipe.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Add water, honey, oil and salt; stir until dissolved.
Sprinkle yeast on top, let sit 15 minutes or until yeast starts to bubble. Add flour; add additional flour as needed.
Knead for 10 minutes. Let rise 1 hour, make into loaves or buns.
Rise 1 hour and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 4 loaves of bread, rolls, etc.

title: lemon-apricot parfaits
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in apricot nectar, lemon peel and juice.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour into a bowl and place in refrigerator or freezer for 15 to 30 minutes to chill quickly.

title: shish kebab
directions: Marinate meat in dressing in plastic bag from 1 hour to overnight
(can
marinate
vegetables
also).
On each skewer, arrange beef, cherry tomato, onion, bell pepper and mushrooms, repeating until skewer is filled.
Grill over medium hot coals until
done,
turning
once.
Baste
with
marinade as needed. Serve with rice.

title: communion bread
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender or 2 knives.
Sprinkle ice water over mixture, 1 tablespoon at a time, stirring just enough to mix.
Stir into a ball.
Roll out as thinly as possible on a floured surface (1/8-inch thick or less).
Transfer to a cookie sheet.
Use sharp edge of knife to cut into desired size.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, then turn oven off and let bread remain in oven until edges begin to brown.
Remove from oven to cool, then separate pieces and store in airtight container.
This recipe makes 600 pieces if cut 1/2 x 1/4 inch.

title: hot-milk sponge cake
directions: In small saucepan, heat milk until it bubbles around edges of pan.
Remove from heat; set aside.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon-colored. Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is smooth and well blended, about 5 minutes.
At low speed (mixer) blend in flour mixture until smooth.
Add warm milk and vanilla, beating just until combined.
Bake in two 8-inch round pans, 9 x 9-inch pan or 24 cupcake tins at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Delicious!

title: breaded turkey cutlets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place turkey cutlets in a medium bowl. Cover with water.
Add lemon juice.
In a shallow bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except oil.
Mix well.
One at a time, take cutlets from water and dip into crumbs, turning once to coat both sides.
Place cutlets in a shallow baking pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
Drizzle oil over breaded cutlets.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemony color.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add oil and flour which has been sifted with salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add vanilla.
Stir in dates, coconut, pecans and raisins.
Add apples last.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Trim all fat from roast and cube.
Brown meat and bone in a large Dutch oven.
Stir in the next 8 ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 hours.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until meat is tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Use as much onion as needed to taste.
Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Roll on waxed paper covered with parsley flakes.
Then roll into nuts (optional). Chill and serve with crackers.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Place in a large bowl. Make a well in the center and stir sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla into it.
Add milk and stir well.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Roll thin and cut into rounds with cookie cutter or glass.
Sprinkle tops with sugar and bake approximately 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie crust.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican bride cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add salt, flavoring, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Hump in a ball and chill for 1 hour.
Flatten cookies on a cookie sheet and cook.
After removing from oven, roll in powdered sugar.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add nuts.
Drop from teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes five dozen.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Save enough of the grated cheese to sprinkle on top as a topping.
(I usually use an extra cup of cheese.)
Mix and pour into casserole dish or 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix all together except the 1/4 cup sugar and Kisses.
Using teaspoon dough for each, shape into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 minutes.
Take out of oven and press one Kiss on each firmly.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: cooked macaroni and cheese
directions: Make sauce of ingredients.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over cooked macaroni.
Put rest of cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Add butter to water and cook until butter is melted.
Add all the flour at once; stir vigorously until ball forms in center of pan.
Cool a little.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mixture should be stiff.
Put in pastry tube for eclair shape or use eclair pans or cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Split sides and fill when cool.
Frost.
Makes 8 to 12.

title: orange julius
directions: Place in blender and
mix
for
about 30 seconds, until the drink becomes "smooth and foamy".

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix together sugar, evaporated milk, sweetened condensed milk, vanilla, eggs, salt, and peanut butter.
Put into hand or electric freezer canister and add enough milk to bring mixture up to the two-thirds line.
Freeze until firm.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: jiffy cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add remaining liquids; blend well. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until done in a 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
This is not too sweet and real good.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: fast breadsticks
directions: Wash hands!
Take a biscuit, roll it between the palms of your hands to form it into breadstick shape.
(They will not come out quite as long.)

title: pie crust
directions: Mix in usual manner. Put 1 egg in 8-ounce measuring cup. Add water and vinegar. Fill cup to 8-ounces with water. Mix into flour and Crisco mixture. Makes 5 crusts. Wrap each ball in wax paper. What you don't use right away keep in freezer until needed.

title: aunt belle's white cake
directions: No vanilla; it has its own flavor.

title: cheesecake
directions: Boil the water. Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
In a separate bowl, mix the sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Add to Jell-O.
Whip the Pet milk until it makes a peak and mix with the other ingredients.
Melt butter and mix with cracker crumbs. Press crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan to make a crust.
Pour other ingredients on top of crust and refrigerate overnight.

title: gladys' easy party punch
directions: Mix
the
Kool-Aid with sugar and water.
Add pineapple juice and
chill.
When ready to serve, add 1 quart of ginger ale and pour over 1 quart sherbet;	stir well.
Serves 50.

title: banana loaf cake
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.
If no sour milk is available, add a little vinegar to sweet milk.

title: one-bowl chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or into 17 1/4 x 11 1/2-inch pan for brownies. Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: paddy cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage and cook in salted water until desired tenderness; drain and put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Stew onion and bell pepper in tomatoes until tender; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over cabbage and toss.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven until heated through and cheese is melted, about 15 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: nestle crunch cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl. Beat butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar in large mixer bowl until creamy. Beat in egg and vanilla. Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in Nestle Crunch baking pieces. Drop by slightly rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand for 2 minutes. Remove to wire racks to cool completely.

title: dona's dump cake
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, dump pie filling, then open cake mix and dump over fruit.
Pour melted butter over top.
Put in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Great served warm with ice cream.

title: avocado salsa
directions: Halve the tomatoes crosswise and gently squeeze out and discard the liquid and seeds.
Coarsely chop the tomatoes.
In a blender or food processor, combine the tomatoes, jalapenos, lime juice, garlic, and salt and pulse several times.
